{"title_page": "List of solved missing persons cases", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{For|other lists of disappeared persons|Lists of people who disappeared}}\n{{dynamic list}}\n\nThis is a '''list of solved missing persons cases''' of people who went missing in unknown locations or unknown circumstances that were eventually explained by their reappearance or the recovery of their bodies, or the conviction of the perpetrator(s) responsible for their disappearances.\n\n<!--By consensus, entries must be those of people or disappearances that are notable because an article about them already exists. Do not add an entry if you cannot link to such an article.-->\n<!--When adding ages to these tables please note:\n\n* If any person went missing below the age of 10 (i.e. single digits), please use data-sort-value for those persons on the date value to ensure that it is kept at the top. e.g. for an age of 8, use data-sort-value=\"008\"\n* If any person went missing below the age of 1 (i.e. they were X weeks/months old), please use data-sort-value for those persons on the date value to ensure that it is kept at the top. e.g. for an age of 9 weeks, work what proportion of that age was in a year:\n      * Use the formula for age in months (assuming equal length of months):\n            (age in months)/12\n      * Use the formula for age in weeks (assuming 4 weeks in a month):\n            (age in weeks)/(12*4)\n      * Use the formula for age in days (assuming 4 weeks in a month and 7 days per week):\n            (age in days)/(12*4*7)\n\n* If any person in the table was missing above the age of 100, please ensure that ALL of the other dates use data-sort-value. e.g. for an age of 50 use data-sort-value=\"050\"\n\nThis ensures that ages are in the right order\n-->\n{{horizontal TOC|nonum=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n\n==Before 1900==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"isoDate\"|Date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Person(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Age \n! class=\"unsortable\"|Circumstances\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Found alive / cause of death\n! data-sort-type=\"value\"|Time spent missing or unconfirmed\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1553-05-10\"|1553\n|[[Hugh Willoughby|Sir Hugh Willoughby]]\n|\n|Sir Hugh Willoughby, an English explorer, set sail from London on 10 May 1553 to search for a sea route right around the north of Europe and Asia to China. His second-in-command was [[Richard Chancellor]] of Bristol. Off the coast of Norway the two men were separated by a storm. Willoughby's ship ended up stuck in ice off [[S\u00e1pmi|Lapland]] and he and all of his crew died. Their frozen bodies were found the following year.<!-- <ref>{{cite book|last1=Fowke|first1=Bob|title=What They Don't Tell You About The Tudors|date=2001|publisher=[[Hodder Children's Books]] | location=London|isbn=978-0-340-78808-0 | page=88}}</ref> appears incorrect - Wikipedia article shows only 1 year-->\n|No\n|data-sort-value=\"0365\"|1 year\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1660-08-16\"|1660\n|[[The Campden Wonder|William Harrison]]\n|70\n|William Harrison disappeared on 16 August 1660 from the town of [[Chipping Campden]], Gloucestershire and was thought to have been murdered. He resurfaced two years later and said that he had been kidnapped.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-nottinghamshire-37577247|title=Lost girl who helped change the law|last=Watson|first=Greig|date=2017|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-12-21|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210151655/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-nottinghamshire-37577247|archive-date=10 December 2017}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"0730\"|2 years\n|-\n|1892\n|[[Gottlieb Fluhmann]] \n|c. 55\n|The [[Colorado]] rancher was last seen in 1892 before he disappeared under strange and largely unknown circumstances. His body was found in 1944, but the cause of death could not be determined.\n|No / Unknown\n|data-sort-value=\"18980\"|52 years\n|}\n\n==1900\u20131949==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"isoDate\"|Date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Person(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Age \n! class=\"unsortable\"|Circumstances\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Found alive / cause of death\n! data-sort-type=\"value\"|Time spent missing or unconfirmed\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1910-08-20\"|1910\n|[[Crime of Cuenca|Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Grimaldos L\u00f3pez]]\n|28\n|Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Grimaldos L\u00f3pez, a [[shepherd]] from [[Tresjuncos]], Spain, went missing on 20 August 1910. Two men were convicted of his killing after confessing under torture. Grimaldos resurfaced in 1926.<ref>{{Cite web |first=\u00c1ngel Luis L\u00f3pez |last=Villaverde |url=http://www.uclm.es/ceclm/publicaciones/rp_clm03.htm |title=El crimen de Cuenca en treinta art\u00edculos: antolog\u00eda period\u00edstica del error judicial |trans-title=The crime of Cuenca in thirty articles: journalistic anthology of judicial error |publisher=[[University of Castilla\u2013La Mancha|Universidad de Castilla\u2013La Mancha]] |date=2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222162608/https://previa.uclm.es/ceclm/publicaciones/rp_clm03.htm |archive-date=22 December 2017 |access-date=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"5,613\"|16 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1911-04-08\"|1911\n|[[Elsie Paroubek]]\n|data-sort-value=\"005\"|5\n|Elsie Paroubek was a [[Czech American]] girl who disappeared in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]], on 8 April 1911. On 9 May 1911, employees of the [[Lockport, Illinois|Lockport]] power plant near [[Joliet, Illinois|Joliet]], thirty-five miles outside of Chicago, saw a body floating in the [[Chicago Sanitary and Ship Canal]], which was identified as hers.<ref>\"The \"gypsies\" had left Round Lake when we reached there and we traced them to Volo, Illinois, and then to McHenry, where we found the band,\" said Det. Sheehan. \"They had a girl about 5-years old with them, but she was not the missing child. Instead of having blond hair as reported by a number of persons, she had deep black hair and the dark complexion of the gypsies. She was the daughter of one of the gypsies and there was no other girl in the band.\" \"Return: Quest for Girl in Vain\". ''Chicago Daily News'', 15 April 1911, p. 2.</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0031\"|31 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1913-02-09\"|1913\n|Captain [[Robert Falcon Scott]] & his group\n|\n|Captain Scott and his party of explorers were found 13 months after their disappearance on their [[South Pole]] expedition.\n|No / [[Hypothermia]] & starvation\n|data-sort-value=\"0396\"|13 months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1926-12\"|1926\n|[[Agatha Christie]]\n|36\n|Agatha Christie, a famous British crime writer, [[Agatha_Christie#Disappearance:_1926|famously disappeared]] in December 1926, after her husband asked for a divorce. She was located alive 10 days later in a [[Yorkshire]] health spa, and always refused to give an explanation.<ref>{{Cite news |title=MRS. CHRISTIE FOUND IN A YORKSHIRE SPA; Missing Novelist, Under an Assumed Name, Was Staying at a Hotel There. CLUE A NEWSPAPER PICTURE Mystery Writer Is Victim of Loss of Memory, Her Husband Declares. MRS. CHRISTIE FOUND IN A YORKSHIRE SPA |newspaper=New York Times |date=15 December 1926 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1926/12/15/archives/mrs-christie-found-in-a-yorkshire-spa-missing-novelist-under-an.html |accessdate=16 September 2009}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"0010\"|10 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1928-01-01\"|1928  \n|[[Walter Collins]] \n|9\n|Collins disappeared from his home in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]], in 1928. He was later determined to have been murdered by [[Gordon Stewart Northcott]] in what was known as the [[Wineville Chicken Coop Murders]]. His disappearance and the attempt by the Los Angeles police department to convince his mother that a different boy was her son formed the basis of the 2008 film ''[[Changeling (film)|Changeling]]''.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/465341642.html?dids=465341642:465341642&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&date=Apr+04%2C+1928pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=New+Kidnaping+Clew+Furnished+in+Hunt+for+Missing+Collins+Boy New Kidnaping Clew Furnished in Hunt for Missing Collins Boy] ''Los Angeles Times'' 4 April 1928.</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Foundas |first=Scott |title=Clint Eastwood: The Set Whisperer \u2013 Shooting quietly on the Changeling set |newspaper=[[LA Weekly]] |date=December 19, 2007 |url=http://www.laweekly.com/film+tv/film/clint-eastwood-the-set-whisperer/17910/ |access-date=December 29, 2007 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20071223025728/http://www.laweekly.com/film+tv/film/clint-eastwood-the-set-whisperer/17910/ |archive-date=December 23, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=King |first=Susan |author-link=Susan King (journalist) |title=Changeling actor reveres his boss: Clint Eastwood |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=September 7, 2008 |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2008/sep/07/entertainment/ca-changeling7 |access-date=September 5, 2008}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"730\"|2 years<!-- ? estimate -->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1932-03-01\"|1932\n|[[Lindbergh kidnapping|Charles Augustus Lindbergh Jr.]]\n|1\n|On March 1, 1932, Charles Augustus Lindbergh Jr., 20-month-old son of aviator [[Charles Lindbergh]] and [[Anne Morrow Lindbergh]], was abducted from the crib in the upper floor of his home in [[Highfields (Amwell and Hopewell, New Jersey)|Highfields]] in [[East Amwell, New Jersey|East Amwell]], [[New Jersey]], [[United States]].<ref>{{Cite news | first=Barbara |last=Gill |title=Lindbergh kidnapping rocked the world 50 years ago |work=[[The Hunterdon County Democrat]]  |year=1981 |accessdate=December 30, 2008 |quote=So while the world's attention was focused on Hopewell, from which the first press dispatches emanated about the kidnapping, the Democrat made sure its readers knew that the new home of Col. Charles A. Lindbergh and Anne Morrow Lindbergh was in East Amwell Township, Hunterdon County. |url=http://www.nj.com/lindbergh/hunterdon/index.ssf?/lindbergh/stories/demcovr.html |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On May 12, the child's corpse was discovered by a truck driver by the side of a nearby road.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aiuto |first=Russell |title=The Theft of the Eaglet |work=The Lindbergh Kidnapping |publisher=TruTv |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/notorious_murders/famous/lindbergh/index_1.html |accessdate=June 24, 2009 |df=dmy-all |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090601183654/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/notorious_murders/famous/lindbergh/index_1.html |archive-date=1 June 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Lindbergh Kidnapping Index |url=http://www.charleslindbergh.com/kidnap/ |accessdate=October 16, 2013 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|No / Murder\n|data-sort-value=\"072\"|72 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1934-08-27\"|1934\n|[[Linda Agostini]]\n|28\n|Linda Agostini was a woman who emigrated from [[South London|South East London]] to Australia, and disappeared from Melbourne on 27 August 1934. A body, not identified as hers until 1944, was found in a culvert beside a rural road in [[Albury]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]], in September 1934.<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/agostini-linda-9966|title=Australian Dictionary of Biography|last=Pennay|first=Bruce|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University|location=Canberra|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806152536/http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/agostini-linda-9966|archive-date=6 August 2017|chapter=Agostini, Linda (1905\u20131934)}}</ref>\n|No / Manslaughter\n|data-sort-value=\"3414\"|10 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1938-12-17\"|1938\n|[[Murder of Margaret Martin|Margaret Martin]]\n|19 \n|Margaret Martin was a woman from [[Kingston, Pennsylvania]], who went missing on 17 December 1938, and was found dead in [[Wyoming County, Pennsylvania]], several days later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://citizensvoice.com/news/kingston-resident-s-1938-slaying-remains-unsolved-1.1619195|title=Kingston resident's 1938 slaying remains unsolved|last=Nissley|first=Erin|access-date=2017-09-23|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923195308/http://citizensvoice.com/news/kingston-resident-s-1938-slaying-remains-unsolved-1.1619195|archive-date=23 September 2017|date=19 January 2014}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"004\"|Several days <!-- [presume 4 for now] -->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1944-07\"|1944\n|[[Shoichi Yokoi]]\n|29\n|Shoichi Yokoi was a Japanese [[sergeant]] in the [[Imperial Japanese Army]] (IJA) during the [[Second World War]], who disappeared in July 1944,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-16681636|title=Shoichi Yokoi, the Japanese soldier who held out in Guam|last=Lanchin|first=Mike|date=24 January 2012|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-08-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> and on the evening of 24 January 1972, Yokoi was discovered alive in the jungle.<ref name=\"Mendoza1999\">{{cite book|author=Patrick M. Mendoza|title=Extraordinary People in Extraordinary Times: Heroes, Sheroes, and Villains|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=g6nQjEr84uMC&pg=PA71|year=1999|publisher=Libraries Unlimited|isbn=978-1-56308-611-3|page=71}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"10068\"|28 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1944-12\"|1944\n|[[Hiroo Onoda]] \n|51 or 52\n|Hiroo Onoda was an [[Imperial Japanese Army]] [[Military intelligence|intelligence]] officer who fought in [[World War II]], disappeared in December 1944, and resurfaced in March 1974.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/wwii-soldier-who-hid-in-jungle-for-29-years-dies-at-91/|title=WWII soldier who hid in jungle for 29 years dies at 91|access-date=2017-09-12|language=en|date=17 January 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913044331/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/wwii-soldier-who-hid-in-jungle-for-29-years-dies-at-91/|archive-date=13 September 2017}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"10682\"|30 years\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1945\"|1945\n|[[Martin Bormann]]\n|45\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Martin Bormann, head of the [[Nazi Party Chancellery]], and Ludwig Stumpfegger, [[Adolf Hitler]]'s personal surgeon, thought to be at large from 2 May 1945 until 1972 when their remains were discovered near the Reichstag, but not confirmed conclusively until 1998.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/dna-test-closes-book-on-mystery-of-martin-bormann-1161449.html|title=DNA test closes book on mystery of Martin Bormann|date=4 May 1998|work=The Independent|access-date=2018-01-05|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107013555/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/dna-test-closes-book-on-mystery-of-martin-bormann-1161449.html|archive-date=7 November 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Suicide\n|rowspan=\"1\" data-sort-value=\"19357\"|58 years\n|-\n|[[Ludwig Stumpfegger]]\n|34\n|rowspan=\"1\" data-sort-value=\"19357\"|58 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1948\"|1948\n|[[Placido Rizzotto]]\n|34\n|Rizzotto was a [[Italian Resistance|partisan]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lombardia.anpi.it/voghera/rizzotto/rizzotto.htm|title=ANPI Voghera &#124; Placido Rizzotto \u2013 Il Partigiano che mor\u00ec di mafia|website=lombardia.anpi.it}}</ref> [[socialist]] peasant and [[trade union]] leader from [[Corleone]], who was assassinated by [[Sicilian Mafia]] boss [[Luciano Leggio]] on 10 March 1948. Over 60 years after his death, remains were found on 7 July 2009, on a cliff in [[Rocca Busambra]] near Corleone, and on 9 March 2012, a [[DNA test]], compared with one extracted from his father Carmelo Rizzotto, long dead and exhumed for this purpose, confirmed the identity of remains as being that of Placido Rizzotto following a long and difficult investigation conducted by the [[Polizia di Stato|State Police]] at the service of the PS Commissariat of Corleone.<ref name=\"palermo_repubblica_it\" >{{Cite web|url=http://palermo.repubblica.it/cronaca/2012/03/09/news/trovate_le_ossa_di_placido_rizzotto-31212133/|title=Ritrovati i resti di Placido Rizzotto sindacalista ucciso dalla mafia nel '48 \u2013 Palermo \u2013 Repubblica.it|website=Palermo \u2013 La Repubblica}}</ref><ref name=\"corriere_it\" >{{Cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/12_marzo_09/rizzotto-identificati-resti-corleone_8ae8bfea-69b8-11e1-b42a-aa1beb6952a8.shtml|title=Identificati dopo 64 anni i resti di Rizzotto il sindacalista che combatteva la mafia di Liggio|first=Redazione|last=Online|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"22399\"|61 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1949\"|1949\n|[[Josef Mengele]]\n|38\n|Josef Mengele was a German SS officer and physician in [[Auschwitz concentration camp]], fled to Argentina in 1949 to escape prosecution and took several false identities. His whereabouts became known in 1985 after the West German prosecutor's office received a tip. He drowned while swimming in 1979 and was buried under a false name in Brazil.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/06/22/world/scientists-decide-brazil-skelton-is-josef-mengele.html|title=Scientists Decide Brazil Skelton Is Josef Mengele|last=Blumenthal|first=Ralph|date=22 June 1985|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-01-04|last2=Times|first2=Special to the New York|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180402213559/https://www.nytimes.com/1985/06/22/world/scientists-decide-brazil-skelton-is-josef-mengele.html?mtrref=web.archive.org|archive-date=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n|No / Drowning\n|data-sort-value=\"13515\"|37 years\n|}\n\n==1950\u20131979==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"isoDate\"|Date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Person(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Age \n! class=\"unsortable\"|Circumstances\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Found alive / cause of death\n! data-sort-type=\"value\"|Time spent missing or unconfirmed\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1951-08\"|1951\n|[[Bill Barilko]]\n|24 \n|rowspan=\"2\"|Bill Barilko, a player for the [[Toronto Maple Leafs]] hockey team, disappeared in August 1951 while returning from a fishing trip at [[Seal River (Ontario)|Seal River, Ontario]]. He was with his dentist, Henry Hudson, flying aboard Hudson's [[Fairchild 24]] floatplane at the time of their disappearance. Barilko and Hudson remained missing for 11 years until the plane's wreckage was found {{convert|56|mi}} [[Flight plan|off course]] north of [[Cochrane, Ontario]], partially burned and submerged in a swamp with the men found still strapped in their seats.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vyhnak|first1=Carola|title=The 11-year mystery of Leafs' 'Bashin' Bill Barilko' {{!}} Toronto Star|url=https://www.thestar.com/yourtoronto/once-upon-a-city-archives/2017/06/01/the-11-year-mystery-of-leafs-bashin-bill-barilko.html|accessdate=7 April 2018|work=The Toronto Star|date=1 June 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>Victims of Aviation Accidents or Incidents in Canada: Cal Jones, Billy Joe Booth, Jonathan Mann, Brice Herbert Goldsborough, Bill Barilko, {{ISBN|978-1-155-40830-9}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Plane crash\n|data-sort-value=\"4015\"|11 years\n|-\n|Henry Hudson\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"4015\"|11 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1951-04-19\"|1951\n|[[Philip Mangano]]\n|53\n|A mafia [[underboss]] of the future [[Gambino crime family]], his brother [[Vincent Mangano]] disappeared on the same day that Philip Mangano's body was found in [[Jamaica Bay]] (his brother's body was never found). He is believed to have been killed on the orders of [[Albert Anastasia]] as part of a coup.<ref name=\"shot dead\">{{cite news|title=Aide of Joe Adonis is Found Shot Dead|url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1951/04/20/87242113.pdf|accessdate=26 February 2012|newspaper=New York Times|date=April 20, 1951}}</ref> He was murdered along with his brother on the orders of family [[underboss]] [[Albert Anastasia]] in [[Brooklyn]] in 1951.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lacndb.com/php/Info.php?name=Family+-+Gambino+(Mangano)|title=La Cosa Nostra|website=www.lacndb.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://crime.about.com/od/gangsters/ig/Mafia-Mug-Shots/mangano_vincent.htm|title=Vincent Mangano|newspaper=About.com News & Issues|access-date=27 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/crime/family-gambinos-gallery-1.14318?pmSlide=1.14398|title=All in the Family: Inside the Gambinos \u2013 slide 5|newspaper=Daily News|location=New York|access-date=27 November 2016}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|<!-- not enough information -->\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1953-05-17\"|1953\n|[[Kyllikki Saari]]\n|17\n|Kyllikki Saari, a girl from Finland, was last seen alive on 17 May 1953 cycling home from a prayer meeting. Kyllikki's bicycle was recovered in a [[marsh]] that summer and her remains were found on 11 October 1953 in a [[bog]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://imgur.com/gallery/Bnqql|title=Unsolved murders: The Bog Grave|work=Imgur|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0147\"|147 days\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" data-sort-value=\"1954-06-10\"|1954\n|Eugene Lindsey\n|45\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Father and son Eugene and Richard Lindsey, and their friend Frederick Claar, were last seen on June 12, 1954 in the [[Gasp\u00e9 Peninsula|Gasp\u00e9]] region of Quebec, where they had driven to from [[Hollidaysburg, Pennsylvania]] on a hunting trip. Eugene Lindsey's body was discovered in deep bush a month later (July 15) and those of the other two men on July 23, some 4 kilometres away. Their clothes had bullet holes in them. The discoveries led to the arrest of a prospector named [[Wilbert Coffin]] and his conviction based on circumstantial evidence. He was eventually hanged. The case is well known in Canada as the [[Coffin Affair]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070322093151/http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/features/onlineextras/news/story.html?id=5c9ac7d5-69b9-46a9-afdf-5422194f1467 Was the Wrong Man Hanged?] ''Montreal Gazette'', August 16, 2006]</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0033\"|33 days\n|-\n|Richard Lindsey\n|17\n|data-sort-value=\"0041\"|41 days\n|-\n|Frederick Claar\n|19\n|data-sort-value=\"0041\"|41 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1955\"|1955\n|[[Curtis Chillingworth]]\n|58 \n|Curtis Chillingworth was a Florida attorney and [[United States federal judge|state judge]] who disappeared from his [[Manalapan, Florida]] home in 1955. He was later discovered to have been murdered though his body was never recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biographies.net/people//en/curtis_chillingworth|title=Biography of Curtis Chillingworth|website=www.biographies.net|language=en|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0000\"|never found\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1956-12-18\"|1956\n|Barbara Grimes\n|15\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Murder of the Grimes sisters|Barbara and Patricia Grimes]] were teenage sisters who disappeared from the Brighton Park, Chicago, Illinois area on 28 December 1956 while returning home from a movie. Their bodies were found on 22 January 1957 down an embankment off a roadway.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/crime/elvis-presley-loving-grimes-sisters-found-dead-60-years-article-1.2922567|title=Elvis Presley-loving Grimes sisters found dead 60 years ago|work=NY Daily News|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0025\"|25 days\n|-\n|Patricia Grimes\n|13\n|data-sort-value=\"0025\"|25 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1957-02-25\"|1957\n|[[Death of Mary Jane Barker|Mary Jane Barker]]\n|data-sort-value=\"004\"|4\n|Mary Jane Barker, a girl from [[Bellmawr, New Jersey]], went missing on 25 February 1957 along with her playmate's dog.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/2691572/the_newsherald/|title=Clipped From The News-Herald|date=5 March 1957|work=The News-Herald|access-date=2017-07-16|pages=12}}</ref> Barker was found dead in the closet of a vacant house near her home on 3 March 1957 after becoming trapped with the dog who survived.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1957/03/04/page/1/article/missing-girl-4-found-dead|title=Missing Girl 4, Found Dead (March 4, 1957)|access-date=2017-07-16}}</ref> \n|No / Starvation\n|data-sort-value=\"0006\"|6 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1957-03-15\"|1957\n|[[Lawrence Joseph Bader]]\n|30 \n|Lawrence Joseph Bader was a cookware salesman from [[Akron, Ohio]] who disappeared on a fishing trip on 15 March 1957 in [[Lake Erie]]. Eight years later he was found alive in [[Omaha, Nebraska]] working as a local TV personality named \"Fritz\" Johnson. He died from a brain tumor a year later leaving six children from two wives. It has been debated but never determined whether he was an amnesiac, had multiple personalities, or was simply a hoaxer.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KkEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA41|title=LIFE|last=Inc|first=Time|date=5 March 1965|publisher=Time Inc|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8NybAAAACAAJ|title=Among the Missing: An Anecdotal History of Missing Persons from 1800 to the Present|last=Nash|first=Jay Robert|date=1 January 1978|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9780671240059|language=en}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"2920\"|8 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1957-12-03\"|1957\n|[[Murder of Maria Ridulph|Maria Ridulph]]\n|data-sort-value=\"0007\"|7 \n|Maria Ridulph was an American girl who disappeared on 3 December 1957 from a street corner in her neighborhood in [[Sycamore, Illinois]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/11/us/maria-ridulphs-killer-gets-life-55-years-after-her-death.html|title=Maria Ridulph's Killer Gets Life 55 Years After Her Death|last=Goode|first=Erica|date=10 December 2012|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Her body was found in [[Woodbine, Illinois|Woodbine]], 100 miles from her home, on 26 April 1958.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://idnc.library.illinois.edu/cgi-bin/illinois?a=d&d=STR19580429.2.6#|title=True Republican 29 April 1958 \u2013 Illinois Digital Newspaper Collections|website=idnc.library.illinois.edu|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0144\"|144 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1958\"|1958\n|[[Ishinosuke Uwano]] \n|35 to 36\n|Ishinosuke Uwano is a former soldier in the [[Japanese Imperial Army]] who disappeared in 1958 and was found living in [[Ukraine]] in April 2006.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4916294.stm|title=Japanese WWII soldier found alive|date=18 April 2006|access-date=2017-09-12|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"17520\"|48 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1961\"|1961\n|[[Lucy Ann Johnson]] \n|25\n|Lucy Ann Johnson disappeared in 1961 from [[British Columbia]], Canada but was not reported missing by her family until 1965. In 2013 she was found alive in [[Yukon]], Canada, having started a new family after her disappearance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Missing mom found alive in Canada after more than 50 years|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2013/07/20/missing-mom-found-alive-in-canada-after-more-than-50-years/|accessdate=20 July 2013|publisher=Fox News|date=20 July 2013}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"18980\"|52 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1965\"|1965\n|[[Ajjamada B. Devaiah]] \n|32 or 33\n|Ajjamada B. Devaiah, an [[Indian Air Force]] pilot, was shot down in an [[aerial dogfight]] in 1965 over [[Pakistan]]. The Indian Air Force was unaware of what happened and declared him missing. It was revealed much later by Pakistan sources, based on a 1979 book by John Fricker, that Devayya's body was found almost intact by villagers not very far from [[Sargodha]] and buried. He was decorated posthumously in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|title=Squadron Leader Ajammada Boppaya Devayya|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/IAF/Database/4810|publisher=Bharat Rakshak|accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref>\n|No / [[Killed in action]]\n|data-sort-value=\"5110\"|14 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1967-03-16\"|1967\n|[[Alvar Larsson]]\n|13\n|Alvar Larsson was a [[Swedes|Swedish]] boy who disappeared on 16 April 1967 while going for a walk.<ref name=\"Google Translate\">{{Cite web|url=https://translate.google.ca/translate?sl=sv&u=http://29juli1965.blogspot.com/2016/05/alvar-larsson-forsvann-1967-vad-hande.html|title=Google Translate|website=translate.google.ca|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://s1033.photobucket.com/user/daCosta_arkivet/library/Ovrigt/Alvar%20Larsson%201967?sort=3&page=1|title=Alvar Larsson 1967 by daCosta_arkivet|work=Photobucket|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref> In November 1982 a human skull was found on a small island 6&nbsp;km away that was identified as belonging to Larsson.<ref name=\"Google Translate\"/>\n|No\n|data-sort-value=\"5678\"|15 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1967-12-06\"|1967\n|[[Barbara Ann Hackmann Taylor]]\n|24\n|Barbara Ann Hackmann Taylor disappeared on 6 December 1967 and was found dead near [[Georgetown, Kentucky]] on 17 May 1968.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1696&dat=19980423&id=9PEaAAAAIBAJ&pg=6796,2875583|title=Doaily News|website=news.google.com|access-date=2017-08-25}}</ref> Her unidentified body found wrapped in canvas, similar to that used for a tent, and she was dubbed \"Tent Girl\". The son-in-law of the man who discovered her body had an interest in the case and contacted her relatives after seeing a missing persons report. Barbara Taylor's remains were positively identified in 1998 following DNA testing.  \n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0163\"|163 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1969-11-14\"|1969\n|[[Murder of Reet Jurvetson|Reet Jurvetson]]\n|19\n|Reet Jurvetson, a [[Canadian Americans|Canadian-American]] woman disappeared on 14 November 1969 and was found murdered on 16 November 1969 in a dense bushland off [[Mulholland Drive]] in Los Angeles, California. She had been stabbed over 150 times and her body was rolled down an embankment. Jurvetson remained unidentified for 46 years until an online mortuary photograph was recognised by her family and friends.<ref name=\"could\">{{cite news|last1=Siemaszko|first1=Corky|title=Reet Jurvetson, Killed in 1969, Could Be a Manson Family Murder Victim|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/reet-jurvetson-killed-1969-could-be-manson-family-murder-victim-n564106|accessdate=7 September 2016|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=28 April 2016}}</ref> \n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"16790\"|46 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1969\"|1969\n|[[Murder of Reyna Marroquin|Reyna Marroquin]]\n|27\n|Reyna Marroquin, a pregnant [[Salvadoran]] woman, disappeared in 1969 from [[Nassau County, New York]]. Her remains were found on 2 September 1999 in the former [[Jericho, New York|Jericho]], [[New York (state)|New York]] home of Howard B. Elkins, her former boss, sealed in a drum that was stored in a crawl space. Marroquin was having an affair with Elkins and DNA test showed that Elkins was the father of the fetus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/missing-for-30-years/|title=Missing For 30 Years|access-date=2017-08-28|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://truecrimetruant.com/index.php/tag/reyna-marroquin/|title=Reyna Marroquin \u2013 True Crime Truant|website=truecrimetruant.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2000-01-22/news/0001220143_1_elkins-unborn-child-dna|title=Dna Links Suicide To Killing|work=tribunedigital-sunsentinel|access-date=2017-08-28|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"10950\"|30 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1970-09-24\"|1970\n|[[Jacques Verg\u00e8s]]\n|\n|Jacques Verg\u00e8s, a French-Vietnamese lawyer, left his wife [[Djamila Bouhired]] and cut off all ties with friends and family. He was last seen on 24 February 1970 until he reappeared in 1978 and refused to explain his disappearance or whereabouts during that period.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/law-obituaries/10247180/Jacques-Verges.html|title=Jacques Verg\u00e8s|work=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2017-08-12|language=en}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"2920\"|8 years \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1970-06-22\"|1970\n|Harvey Crewe\n|28\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Harvey and Jeannette Crewe]], a New Zealand farming couple, were reported missing from their bloodstained farmhouse at [[Pukekawa]], [[Waikato Plains|Lower Waikato]] on 22 June 1970 where their unharmed 18-month-old daughter was found in her cot. Jeannette Crewe's body was found, wrapped in a duvet and bound with copper wire, in the [[Waikato River]] on 16 August 1970 and her husband's body was retrieved upriver on 16 September 1970.<ref>\"Forensic History: Crimes, Frauds, and Scandals\" by Professor Elizabeth A Murray</ref> The initial indications from the crime scene pointed to foul play, occurring between 17 and 22 June, but it was not until the bodies were recovered that it was established that both had been shot to death.<ref>{{citation |url=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/r.christie/thomas_royal_commission_1980.pdf |title=Report of the Royal Commission to Inquire into the Circumstances of the Convictions of Arthur Allan Thomas for the Murders of David Harvey Crewe and Jeanette Lenore Crewe, 1980 |accessdate=12 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609174212/http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/r.christie/thomas_royal_commission_1980.pdf |archive-date=9 June 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0086\"|86 days \n|-\n|Jeannette Crewe\n|30\n|data-sort-value=\"0055\"|55 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1970-11\"|1970\n|[[Ronald Hughes]]\n|35\n|Ronald Hughes was an American attorney who represented [[Charles Manson|Manson family]] member [[Leslie Van Houten]] and disappeared in November 1970 during a camping trip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://macewen2013.wordpress.com/2014/07/02/a-hell-of-a-hoax-part-4-the-missing-attorney-and-more-murders/|title=A Hell of a Hoax! Part 4: The Missing Attorney and More Murders|last=macewen2013|date=2 July 2014|website=Bone Speak|access-date=2017-07-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2012/jun/01/local/la-me-manson-tapes-20120601/2|title=Manson follower's tapes may yield new clues, LAPD says|last=Becerra|first=Hector|date=1 June 2012|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-07-23|last2=Winton|first2=Richard|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> On 29 March 1971 his body was found by two fishermen in [[Ventura County]] wedged between two boulders in a gorge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cielodrive.com/archive/tate-lawyers-body-believed-to-be-found/|title=Tate Lawyers Body Believed To Be Found \u2013 Charles Manson Family and Sharon Tate-Labianca Murders Archive|website=www.cielodrive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-23}}</ref>\n|No\n|data-sort-value=\"0150\"|5 months \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1971\"|1971\n|[[Shelagh McDonald]] \n|24\n|Shelagh McDonald, a Scottish folk singer and songwriter, vanished in 1971. Following the reissue of two of her albums on CD in the mid-2000s, articles were written about her work and disappearance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mystery woman|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/mystery-woman-294201.html|website=The Independent|accessdate=10 May 2018|date=23 June 2005}}</ref> In 2005, McDonald read one of these articles and she contacted the press to explain that following an [[Lysergic acid diethylamide|LSD]] trip, which had left her with long-term severe flashbacks and disorientation, she had returned to her family who kept her isolated while she recovered.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shelagh McDonald, Vanished Singer/Songwriter Feared Dead for Decades, Is Alive and Singing...|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/charles-donovan/shelagh-mcdonald_b_4574222.html|website=HuffPost UK|accessdate=10 May 2018|date=10 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=McDonald|first1=Shelagh|title=Experience: I disappeared for 30 years|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2013/oct/12/experience-i-disappeared-for-30-years|website=the Guardian|accessdate=10 May 2018|language=en|date=12 October 2013}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"12410\"|34 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1971-07-11\"|1971\n|[[Murders of Rhonda Johnson and Sharon Shaw|Rhonda Johnson and Sharon Shaw]]\n|13 and 14\n|Rhonda Renee Johnson and Sharon Lynn Shaw were two teenage girls who disappeared in [[Harris County, Texas]], on the afternoon of 4 August 1971. In early 1972, skeletal remains of both girls were discovered in and around [[Clear Lake (Galveston Bay)|Clear Lake]] near [[Galveston Bay]]. A local man, Michael Lloyd Self, was charged with their murders in 1972 and convicted of Shaw's murder in 1975. Controversy arose in 1998 when [[serial killer]] Edward Harold Bell confessed to the murders. Bell's confession\u2014and [[Corroborating evidence|corroborating]] [[Witness statement|statements]] from both law enforcement and prosecutors that Self had been coerced into a [[false confession]]\u2014led many to believe that Self had been [[List of wrongful convictions in the United States|wrongfully convicted]].<ref name=cold>{{cite web|url=http://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/article/Confessions-of-a-cold-blooded-killer-2187501.php|work=Houston Chronicle|title=Confessions of a cold-blooded killer|author=Olsen, Lise|date=August 31, 2015|accessdate=November 26, 2016}}</ref> Self died in prison of cancer in 2000.\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0180\"|~6 months \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1972-07-11\"|1972\n|[[Dolores Della Penna]]\n|17\n|Dolores Della Penna was a school girl from [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania who went missing on 11 July 1972. Her limbs and torso were later found in different parts of [[New Jersey]] a week later but her head was never found. She had allegedly been abducted by a gang of drug dealers who accused her of stealing from them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mauryzlevy.wordpress.com/2011/02/02/dead-end-at-toms-river-a-bizarre-murder-mystery/|title=Dead End at Toms River: A Bizarre Murder Mystery|date=2 February 2011|website=Maury Z. Levy: Greatest Hits, Volume One|access-date=2017-04-25}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0007\"|7 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1972-08-07\"|1972\n|[[Jeannette DePalma]]\n|16\n|Jeannette DePalma was a girl who disappeared on 7 August 1972 after telling her mother she was going to visit a friend. Her body was discovered on 19 September 1972 and it is believed she was killed some time around 7 August in [[Springfield Township, Union County, New Jersey|Springfield Township, New Jersey]].<ref>\"Coffeehouse Aides Discount Murder Tie-In\". The Elizabeth Daily Journal. 3 October 1972.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://swordandscale.com/the-unsolved-murder-of-jeannette-depalma/|title=The Unsolved Murder of Jeannette DePalma|date=14 August 2015|work=Sword and Scale|access-date=2017-08-04|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0043\"|43 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1972-12-04\"|1972\n|[[Steven Stayner]]\n|data-sort-value=\"007\"|7\n|Steven Stayner was abducted from the [[Central California]] city and county of [[Merced, California]] on 4 December 1972 by a man named [[Kenneth Parnell]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1989/09/18/us/former-captive-of-molester-is-killed-in-a-hit-run-crash.html|title=Former Captive of Molester Is Killed in a Hit-Run Crash|last=Ap|date=18 September 1989|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-08-24|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He escaped on 1 March 1980 with [[Timothy White (abduction victim)|Timothy White]] who was also abducted by Parnell.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nx2.com/a/nano/36-years-ago-steven-stayner-escaped-his-kidnapper-after-7-years-to-save-another-boys-life-5224|title=36 Years Ago, Steven Stayner Escaped His Kidnapper After 7 Years To Save Another Boy's Life|last=NX2|work=nx2.com|access-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824134320/http://www.nx2.com/a/nano/36-years-ago-steven-stayner-escaped-his-kidnapper-after-7-years-to-save-another-boys-life-5224|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"2644\"|7 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1973-01-27\"|1973\n|[[Murder of Dawn Magyar|Dawn Magyar]]\n|20\n|Dawn Magyar was abducted while she was grocery shopping in [[Owosso, Michigan]] in [[Shiawassee County]] on 27 January 1973 and her body was discovered in a wooded area in [[Saginaw County, Michigan]] on 4 March 1973.<ref name=Press>{{cite news|last=Hornus|first=Tony|title=Dawn Magyar Murder Suspect Was Arrested By Police March 7|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1988&dat=20011231&id=-AgoAAAAIBAJ&pg=3149,5373822|accessdate=16 May 2012|newspaper=[[Argus-Press]] |location=[[Owosso, Michigan]]| date=8 March 2001}}</ref> The case was resolved 28 years after her body was found when a DNA match was made of her killer.<ref name=tony>{{cite news|last1=Hornus|first1=Tony|title=Is Dawn Magyar's Alleged Murderer Jerald Wingeart a Serial Rapist?|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1988&dat=20010311&id=L2UiAAAAIBAJ&pg=2852,795645|accessdate=7 March 2015|newspaper=[[Argus-Press]] |location=[[Owosso, Michigan]] |date=11 March 2001}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0036\"|36 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1973-08-01\"|1973\n|[[Disappearance of Peter Wilson|Peter Wilson]]\n|21\n|Peter Wilson was an Irish man who was abducted on 1 August 1973 and killed by the [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]]. After receiving reliable information his remains were found on 2 November 2010 buried at 