n Bull Run Mountain in [[Haymarket, Virginia]] but remained unidentified for 30 years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/06/13/cynthia-gastelle-remains-identified-32-years-later_n_1593611.html|title=Cynthia Gastelle's Remains Identified: 32 Years Later, Cops Link Remains To Missing Woman|date=13 June 2012|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2017-09-26|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/Skeletal-Remains-Missing-Girl-Bull-Run-Mountain.html|title=Remains of Missing Teen IDed After 32 Years|work=NBC4 Washington|access-date=2017-09-26|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"10905\"|30 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1980-05-28\"|1980\n|[[Murder of Dorothy Jane Scott|Dorothy Jane Scott]]\n|32\n|Dorothy Jane Scott disappeared while getting her car on 28 May 1980 in [[Anaheim, California]] after she had taken two co-workers to the hospital. On 6 August 1984 a [[construction worker]] discovered dog and human bones, side by side, about {{convert|30|ft|m|-1}} from Santa Ana Canyon Road.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newspaperarchive.com/anonymous-crime-clipping-aug-16-1984-237346/|title=Santa Ana, California History {{!}} Crime, August 16, 1984|website=newspaperarchive.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref> The human bones were later identified as being Scott's. The identity and motive of her killer or killers remains unknown.<ref name=\"RemainsConfirm\">{{cite news|last1=Evans|first1=Heidi|title=Remains Confirm Family's Fears|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/10010935/dorothy_jane_scott/|accessdate=31 March 2017|work=Los Angeles Times|via=Newspapers.com|date=17 August 1984|page=4}} {{free access}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"1531\"|4 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1980-07-20\"|1980\n|[[Murder of Brenda Gerow|Brenda Gerow]]\n|20\n|Brenda Gerow was an American woman who disappeared on 20 July 1980 after leaving home with her boyfriend at the time. She was found dead in the desert at [[Pima County, Arizona]] on 8 April 1981 but remained unidentified for thirty-four years.\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"12410\"|34 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1980-08-17\"|1980\n|[[Death of Azaria Chamberlain|Azaria Chamberlain]]\n|data-sort-value=\"0.1875\"<!--This value is calculated assuming that there are 4 whole weeks in a month and then doing 9/(12*4) 9 weeks divided by 12 months multiplied by 4 weeks-->|nine-weeks-old \n|An Australian baby girl who disappeared on the night of 17 August 1980 during a family [[Camping|camping trip]] in [[Uluru]]. Although her remains have never been found her mother insisted that a [[dingo]] had taken her from her camping tent. In a trial sensationalized by the media her mother was found guilty of murder and sentenced to life in prison. Her sentence was overturned six years later when Azaria's jacket was found in a dingo lair. Azaria's disappearance was the subject of four inquests, the last of which in 2012, concluded that a dingo had taken and killed her.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/dingo-took-azaria-chamberlain-coroner-finds-20120612-206wt.html|title=Dingo took Azaria Chamberlain, coroner finds|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=12 June 2012}}</ref>\n|No / Animal attack\n| data-sort-value=\"0000\"| never found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1980-10-11\"|1980\n|[[Murder of Marlene Oakes|Marlene Oakes]]\n|25\n|Marlene Oakes disappeared from her residence in Verona, Kentucky after an argument with her husband. She had planned to divorce him after discovering he was sexually abusing the couple's son. Her skull was discovered in 1981 but remained unidentified until 2001. Her husband was sentenced to life in prison for her murder.<ref name=files>Jordan, Michael, dir. \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LNPj6EpkBlE A Daughter's Journey].\" ''[[Forensic Files]]''. Prod. Paul Bourdett. [[TruTV]]. Atlanta, Georgia, 9 Aug. 2004. Television.</ref>\n| No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"7300\"|20 years\n|-\