ion. Her remains were found on 7 December 1989 when workmen unearthed a rolled carpet while installing a garden behind a house. She was identified by her DNA in what is cited as one of the first instances in which DNA technology was used in this way in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pathologist Bernard Knight to stop crime writing|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/wales/8571689.stm|work=[[BBC News]]|date=17 March 2010|accessdate=20 June 2015|first=Neil|last=Prior}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"3080\"|8 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1981-07-27\"|1981\n|[[Murder of Adam Walsh|Adam Walsh]]\n|data-sort-value=\"006\"|6\n|Adam Walsh was an American boy who was [[kidnapping|abducted]] from the Hollywood Mall in [[Hollywood, Florida]], on 27 July 1981. His severed head was found two weeks later in a drainage canal alongside [[Florida's Turnpike]] in rural [[St. Lucie County, Florida]]. Drifter [[Otis Toole]] confessed to Adam's murder, but due to poor handling by the Hollywood Police he was never convicted of the crime.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/28257294/ns/us_news-crime_and_courts/t/police-killing-adam-walsh-solved/|title=Police: 1981 killing of Adam Walsh solved|date=17 December 2008|work=msnbc.com|access-date=2017-12-21|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"0014\"|2 weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1981-08-17\"|1981\n|[[Dominick Napolitano]]\n|51\n|Organized crime leaders ordered the murder of Dominick Napolitano. Responding to a summons, on August 17, 1981 he went to a meeting, knowing that he would be killed. On August 12, 1982 a body was found at South Avenue and Bridge Street in [[Arlington, Staten Island]] which proved to be Napolitano.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=BcPAL4rXbcgC&pg=PT426&lpg=PT426&dq=August+12,+1982+Dominick+Napolitano+found#v=onepage&q=August+12,+1982+Dominick+Napolitano+found&f=false|title=Donnie Brasco|first=Joseph D.|last=Pistone|date=1 February 1997|publisher=Penguin|via=Google Boo