 found.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10685932|title=Tamihere home in eight days|author=Carolyne Meng-Yee|date=7 November 2010 |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"913\"|2\u00bd years\n|-\n|Heidi Paakkonen\n|21\n|data-sort-value=\"0000\"|not found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1989-10-22\"|1989\n|[[Murder of Jacob Wetterling|Jacob Wetterling]]\n|11\n|Jacob Wetterling was [[Child abduction|abducted]] on 22 October 1989 by a masked gunman while cycling home in the dark with his brother and a friend after going to rent a video from a convenience store in [[St. Joseph, Minnesota]]. His remains were finally found on 1 September 2016, when Danny Heinrich, already serving time on [[child pornography]] charges, led police to them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Authorities confirm: Jacob found|url=http://www.sctimes.com/story/news/local/2016/09/03/authorities-unidentified-remains-found/89825840/|accessdate=4 September 2016|work=SCTimes|date=4 September 2016|location=Saint Cloud, Minnesota}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"9811\"|~29 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1989-10-27\"|1989\n|[[Murder of Amy Mihaljevic|Amy Mihaljevic]]\n|10\n|Amy Mihaljevic, an American [[Elementary school (United States)|elementary school]] student, was [[Kidnapping|kidnapped]] and [[murder]]ed in [[Bay Village, Ohio]] on 27 October 1989. Her body was found on 8 February 1990 in a field off a rural road in [[Ashland County, Ohio|Ashland County]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cleveland.com/opinion/index.ssf/2012/09/investigators_still_chasing_am.html|title=Investigators still chasing Amy Mihaljevic's killer: Brent Larkin|work=cleveland.com|access-date=2017-08-10|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0104\"|3 months\n<!-- |-\n|data-sort-value=\"1989-12-03\"|1989\n|[[Disappearance of Melissa Brannen|Melissa Brannen]]\n|data-sort-value=\"005\"|5\n|Melissa Brannen disappeared on 3 December 1989 from an apartment complex in [[Lorton, Virginia]] while attending a Christmas party there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charleyproject.org/cases/b/brannen_melissa.html|title=The Charley Project: Melissa Lee Brannen|last=Good|first=Meaghan Elizabeth|website=charleyproject.org|access-date=2016-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110190254/http://www.charleyproject.org/cases/b/brannen_melissa.html|archive-date=10 January 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Caleb Hughes was charged and convicted of [[kidnapping]] her.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20114997,00.html|title=Crime and Punishment|publisher=People.com|accessdate=9 December 2014}}</ref>\n|No / Presumed murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0000\"|never found -->\n|-\n|1989\n|[[Elisabeth Brichet]]\n|12\n|Elisabeth Brichet left her friend's house in [[Namur]], Belgium, on the evening of 20 December 1989 and did not arrive home. In 1996, her mother helped organise the [[White March]] in honour of Belgium's missing and murdered children following the arrest of [[Marc Dutroux]]. On 3 July 2004, the girl's remains were found buried in the garden of a [[Donchery]] chateau which formerly belonged to [[Michel Fourniret]] and Monique Olivier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lalibre.be/belgique/retour-sur-le-calvaire-d-elisabeth-brichet-51b73075e4b0de6db9750c70|title=Retour sur le calvaire d'Elisabeth Brichet|first=La|last=Libre.be|date=13 April 2008|website=www.lalibre.be}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"5309\"|14\u00bd years\n|}\n\n==1990s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"isoDate\"|Date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Person(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Age\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Circumstances\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Found alive / cause of death\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1990-05-20\"|1990\n|[[Murder of Susan Poupart|Susan Poupart]]\n|29\n|Susan Poupart, a [[Native Americans in the United States|Native-American]] woman from [[Lac du Flambeau, Wisconsin]], disappeared on 20 May 1990. Her body was found six months later in the [[Chequamegon-Nicolet National Forest]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wjfw.com/stories.html?sku=20140521173520|title=WJFW \u2013 Newswatch 12 Exclusive: Inside the Susan Poupart cold case investigation|website=www.wjfw.com|access-date=2017-08-04}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1991-04-13\"|1991\n|[[Karmein Chan]]\n|13\n|Karmein Chan, an Australian girl who was abducted from her home at night on 13 April 1991 in the [[Melbourne]] suburb of [[Templestowe, Victoria|Templestowe]]; her body was found on 9 April 1992 in [[Edgars Creek Trail|Edgars Creek, Thomastown]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Silvester|first=John|title='Mr Cruel' filmed his victims, say police|url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2006/04/07/1143916721667.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1|accessdate=28 September 2012|newspaper=The Age|date=8 April 2006}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1991-06-10\"|1991\n|[[Kidnapping of Jaycee Dugard|Jaycee Dugard]]\n|11\n|Jaycee Dugard was abducted on 10 June 1991, and was found alive on 26 August 2009 when she turned up at a [[Concord, California]] parole office.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/5-years-later-jaycee-dugard-found-alive-after-18-year-captivity/|title=Five years later: Jaycee Dugard found alive after 18-year captivity|access-date=2017-06-04|language=en}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1991-05-25\"|1991\n|[[Murder of Timothy Wiltsey|Timothy Wiltsey]]\n|5\n|Timothy Wiltsey went missing from [[South Amboy, New Jersey]]; his mother told the police that he went missing from a local carnival on 25 May 1991. Almost a year later, his remains were discovered miles away.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2014/08/post_357.html|title=Timothy Wiltsey: Ten years after the 5-year-old South Amboy boy disappeared|work=NJ.com|access-date=2017-09-15|language=en-US}}</ref> On 18 