ry/4473da4a-df3f-4d19-995c-79c8f51fbe43/|title=THE TROUBLESOME DEATH OF MARGARET PERRY|last=Coll|first=Steve|date=1994-05-08|work=Washington Post|access-date=2019-10-06|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1991-06-29\"|1991\n|[[Murder of Sheree Beasley|Sheree Beasley]]\n|6\n|Sheree Beasley, an Australian schoolgirl from [[Rosebud, Victoria|Rosebud]] was kidnapped, raped, and murdered by a man named Robert Lowe on 29 June 1991,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/south-east/mornington-peninsula-unites-to-mark-rosebud-murder-victim-sheree-beasleys-30th-birthday/news-story/0da24abeaa315042edacd9364ad67291|title=Murdered girl Sheree Beasley remembered|access-date=2017-07-16}}</ref> and her body was found weeks later on 24 September in a [[stormwater drain]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.psychology.org.au/Assets/Files/crime_related_confidentiality_ethics.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=28 January 2015|access-date=2017-07-16|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128115203/http://www.psychology.org.au/Assets/Files/crime_related_confidentiality_ethics.pdf|archivedate=28 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1992-01-05\"|1992 \n|[[John D'Amato]]\n|{{Unknown|align=left}}\n|D'Amato was a New Jersey mobster suspected of homosexual activity disappeared after [[Anthony Capo]] and the other two hitmen entered D'Amato's car to drive to lunch. Sitting in the back seat, Capo shot D'Amato four times, killing him. Capo and Rotundo left the body at a safe house, where other mobsters disposed of it. D'Amato's body was never recovered.<ref>[http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/2006/06/13/2006-06-13_wiseguy_gets_life_for_hit_on.html WISEGUY GETS LIFE FOR HIT ON GAY MOB BOSS] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220064336/http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/2006/06/13/2006-06-13_wiseguy_gets_life_for_hit_on.html |date=February 20, 2009 }} by Thomas Zambito. ''New York Daily News'', June 13, 2006</ref> In 2006, Abramo, Schifilliti and Vitabile were sentenced to [[life imprisonment]] for the murder.\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1992-04-16\"|1992\n|[[Murder of Kristen French|Kristen French]]\n|15\n|Kristen French, a Canadian school girl from [[Ontario]] who disappeared on 16 April 1992, was held captive for three days and then was killed and was found dead on 30 April 1992. She was murdered by [[Karla Homolka]] and [[Paul Bernardo]].\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|rowspan =\"3\" data-sort-value=\"1992-11-13\"|1992\n|[[The Alcasser Girls|Miriam Iborra]]\n|14\n|rowspan=\"3\"|The Alcasser Girls, were three teenage girls from [[Alc\u00e0sser|Alcasser, Spain]], who disappeared on 13 November 1992,<ref name=\"ElPais071292\">[http://elpais.com/diario/1992/12/07/opinion/723682806_850215.html \u00a1Antonia, Desir\u00e9e, Miriam!], El Pa\u00eds, 7 December 1992.</ref> and were found dead on 27 January 1993, and it was revealed that they had been [[kidnapping|kidnapped]], raped, [[Battery (crime)|beaten]], and [[torture]]d after they were abducted.<ref name=\"930128FB\">[http://elpais.com/diario/1993/01/28/espana/728175620_850215.html Hallados los cad\u00e1veres de las tres ni\u00f1as desaparecidas de Alc\u00e0sser con indicios de haber sido asesinadas], Francesc Bayarri, El Pa\u00eds, 28 January 1993.</ref><ref name=\"930129JDFB\">[http://elpais.com/diario/1993/01/29/espana/728262012_850215.html Tres detenidos por el asesinato de las ni\u00f1as de Alc\u00e1sser], Jes\u00fas Duva, Francesc Bayarri, El Pa\u00eds, 29 January 1993.</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|No / Murdered\n|-\n|[[The Alcasser Girls|Antonia Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|15\n|-\n|[[The Alcasser Girls|Desir\u00e9e Folch]]\n|14\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1992-12-28\"|1992\n|[[Katie Beers kidnapping|Katie Beers]]\n|10\n|Katie Beers disappeared on 28 December 1992, during a shopping trip with neighbor John Esposito and was found in a secret room underneath Esposito's home on 13 January 1993. Esposito had been considered a family friend. Prior to the kidnapping she had been the subject of a lengthy custody battle between her mother and godmother and had suffered material deprivation, sexual abuse and hardship.<ref>Diana Jean Schemo, [https://www.nytimes.com/1993/01/17/nyregion/katie-s-ordeal-seeking-friendship-finding-16-days-of-terror.html Katie's Ordeal]. ''New York Times'', 1993-01-17.</ref><ref>J. David Goodman, [https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/16/nyregion/a-girl-held-for-16-days-in-a-dungeon-now-looking-back-as-a-woman.html A Girl Held for 16 Days in a Dungeon, Now Looking Back as a Woman]. ''New York Times'', 15 January 2013.</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1992-11-15\"|1992\n|[[Eugenio Berr\u00edos]]\n|45\n|Eugenio Berr\u00edos, a [[Chileans|Chilean]] [[biochemist]], who worked for the DINA intelligence agency was captured in 1991 escaped to [[Uruguay]] in 1991, at the beginning of the Chilean transition to democracy, who presented himself on 15 November 1992 to a local police office in order to claim he had been kidnapped later disappeared, and what has been identified as his corpse was found in 1995 near [[Montevideo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/13/former-chilean-general-hernan-ramirez-rurange-dies-apparent-suicide|title=Former general under Pinochet dies in apparent suicide days after sentencing|last=Reuters|date=13 August 2015|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-11-20|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1993-05-26\"|1993\n|[[Jayne Furlong]]\n|17\n|Jayne Furlong, a sex worker, was a [[New Zealanders|New Zealander]], who disappeared from a street in [[Auckland]] on 26 May 1993. Her remains were found at a beach in 2012 after being exposed by erosion of a sandbank. She had been abducted and murdered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.police.govt.nz/news/release/31943|accessdate=20 October 2016|title=Long wait ends with sunrise at Sunset Beach|date=20 June 2012|publisher=NZ Police}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1993-08-05\"|1993\n|[[Holly Piirainen]]\n|10\n|Holly Piirainen, an American girl from [[Grafton, Massachusetts]], who disappeared on 5 August 1993. She and her brother had been visiting their grandparents in [[Sturbridge, Massachusetts|Sturbridge]], Massachusetts when Holly was murdered.<ref name=\"Fox Boston\">{{cite news|title=Holly Piirainen: New details emerge in 19-year-old murder case|url=http://www.myfoxboston.com/story/20142417/2012/11/19/new-details-emerge-in-hunt-for-holly-piirainen|newspaper=Fox 25 Boston|date=19 November 2012}}</ref> Piirainen's remains were found by hunters in [[Brimfield, Massachusetts|Brimfield]] on 23 October 1993.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fox25boston.com/news/holly-piirainen-new-details-emerge-in-19yearold-murder-case/139232396|title=Holly Piirainen: New details emerge in 19-year-old murder case|last=EndPlay|date=20 November 2012|work=WFXT|access-date=2017-08-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1993-01-01\"|1993\n|[[Murder of Kori Lamaster|Kori Lamaster]]\n|17\n|Kori Lamaster, an American murder victim who went missing in 1993,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://patch.com/california/santacruz/two-decade-old-pogonip-jane-cold-case-solved-by-santa-cruz-police|title=Two Decade Old 'Pogonip Jane' Cold Case Solved by Santa Cruz Police|date=4 December 2013|work=Santa Cruz, CA Patch|access-date=2017-08-21|language=en-US}}</ref> was found on 29 January 1994, and was not identified until 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kcba.com/2013/12/05/santa-cruz-pogonip-jane-cold-case-murder-takes-ironic-twist/|title=Santa Cruz 'Pogonip Jane' cold case murder takes ironic twist|access-date=2017-08-22}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1994-09-12\"|1994\n|[[Franklin Delano Floyd#Lead up to abduction of Michael Hughes|Michael Anthony Hughes]]\n|6\n|Michael Anthony Hughes was abducted at gunpoint from school on 12 September 1994 by his step father, Franklin Delano Floyd. No trace of the boy has been found.<ref name=Birkbeck>{{cite web|last1=Birkbeck|first1=Matt|title=Finally|url=http://www.mattbirkbeck.com/blog/finally|website=Matt Birkbeck Official Site}}</ref> Floyd is considered a suspect in the hit-and-run death of his wife, whom he had abducted as a child and raised as his daughter. In a 2015 interview with the FBI, Floyd admitted to killing Hughes the same day of the kidnapping,<ref>{{cite web|title=FBI website|url=https://www.fbi.gov/news/stories/cold-case-investigation/cold-case-investigation|accessdate=6 August 2017}}</ref> and is currently on death row for the murder of another woman and the abduction of Michael Hughes.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1994-01-01\"|1994\n|[[Murder of Randi Boothe-Wilson|Randi Boothe-Wilson]]\n|33\n|Randi Boothe-Wilson disappeared from New York when planning to meet family members. Her remains were discovered in December 1995 in North Carolina and were not identified until January 2019.<ref name=\"charley\">{{cite web |last1=Good |first1=Meaghan |title=Randi Stacey Boothe-Wilson |url=http://charleyproject.org/case/randi-stacey-boothe-wilson |website=The Charley Project |accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=id>{{cite news |title=Woman identified in 23-year-old cold case in Jacksonville |url=https://www.witn.com/content/news/Woman-identified-in-23-year-old-cold-case-in-Jacksonville-506379341.html |accessdate=26 February 2019 |work=www.witn.com |language=english}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-01-01\"|1995\n|[[Henning Wehn]]\n|21\n|Henning Wehn was listed by [[Interpol]] as a missing person after disappearing while on holiday in Spain in 1995, while sending mysterious postcards to a friend in Germany. He reappeared in Spain after having traveled to Morocco for three weeks with a man he met on a train.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2DsyUXEH1wM|title=Did the Interpol list Henning Wehn as a missing person? |website=youtube.com|access-date=2017-09-18}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-02-12\"|1995\n|[[Philip Taylor Kramer]]\n|42\n|Philip Taylor Kramer, a computer engineer and former bass guitarist for the rock band [[Iron Butterfly]], disappeared on 12 February 1995 before he was to meet a business partner at the [[Los Angeles International Airport]]; He changed his plans while driving to the airport and asked his guest to meet him at a nearby hotel instead, but failed to appear.<ref name=\"KramerReed\"/> During his travel to and from the airport, Kramer made a flurry of cell phone calls, including to his wife, his Iron Butterfly bandmate [[Ron Bushy]] and finally to the police. In the latter call, Kramer said, \"I'm going to kill myself.\"<ref name=\"KramerReed\">[[Leonard Reed (journalist)|Leonard Reed]], [https://articles.latimes.com/1995-03-30/news/vl-48798_1_taylor-kramer Missing:  Philip (Taylor) Kramer]. ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', 30 March 1995. Retrieved 2016-07-06.</ref> After his phone call to the police, he was never heard from again, which led to an extensive search of the California desert for his vehicle.<ref name=\"KramerReed\"/> On 29 May 1999, Kramer's body was discovered by hikers inside his wrecked minivan at the bottom of a canyon in [[Malibu, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Swanson|first1=Dave|title=The Mysterious Death of Iron Butterfly Bassist Philip Taylor Kramer|url=http://ultimateclassicrock.com/iron-butterfly-philip-taylor-kramer-found-dead/|website=Ultimate Classic Rock|accessdate=7 September 2017}}</ref>\n|No / Suicide\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-05-02\"|1995\n|[[Disappearance of Kiplyn Davis|Kiplyn Davis]]\n|15\n|Kiplyn Davis, high school student who was reported missing on 2 May 1995 in [[Spanish Fork, Utah]]. She is a featured child of the [[Polly Klaas Foundation]]. Several people have been arrested in connection with her murder, although her death has not been confirmed by the discovery of a body.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.good4utah.com/story/d/story/sister-claims-family-covered-up-brothers-role-in-k/34952/T_kkMXFQOE-PrbEznPPU3Q|title=Sister claims family covered up brother's role in Kiplyn Davis murder|work=Good4Utah|accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref> On 11 February 2011, Timmy Brent Olson pleaded guilty to [[manslaughter]] and was sentenced to 15 years in prison. He claimed he saw another individual hit Davis in the head with a rock and helped him move her body, but declined to name the other individual.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ksl.com/?nid=148&sid=14337705/|accessdate=23 March 2017|title=Olsen takes plea deal in Kiplyn Davis case|date=11 February 2011|publisher=ksl.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221112600/http://www.ksl.com/?nid=148&sid=14337705%2F|archive-date=21 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|1995\n|Julie Lejeune and M\u00e9lissa Russo\n|8\n|Eight-year-old friends Julie Lejeune and M\u00e9lissa Russo were reported missing by their families on 24 June 1995 after they left the Russo family home in [[Gr\u00e2ce-Hollogne]], Belgium, and did not return. Their bodies were found buried in the garden of a house in [[Sars-la-Buissi\u00e8re]] on 17 August 1996. After being kidnapped, they had been held in [[Marc Dutroux]]'s house in [[Marcinelle]] for between five and nine months. Locked in the basement, the girls starved to death, Dutroux's wife having neglected them while her husband was in police custody between December 1995 and March 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lalibre.be/belgique/julie-et-melissa-14-mois-de-mysteres-51b8826be4b0de6db9a9d920|title=Julie et M\u00e9lissa,14 mois de myst\u00e8res|first=La|last=Libre.be|date=6 February 2004|website=www.lalibre.be}}</ref>\n|No / Homicide caused by neglect\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-06-01\"|1995\n|[[Death of Jason Callahan|Jason Callahan]]\n|19\n|Jason Callahan made no contact with friends or family after June 1995. The body of a passenger that was found in the wreck of a car on 26 June 1995 was identified as his on 9 December 2015 after his mother formally reported him missing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2015/01/15/mom-reports-son-missing-20-years-after-he-left-to-follow-grateful-dead/|title=Mom reports son missing 20 years after he left to follow Grateful Dead|last=Li|first=David K.|date=15 January 2015|website=New York Post|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.wmbfnews.com/story/30708764/dna-positively-identifies-grateful-doe-as-man-missing-from-myrtle-beach | title=DNA positively identifies 'Grateful Doe' as man missing from Myrtle Beach | work=WMBF News | date=9 December 2015 | agency=NBC | accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=bizarre>{{cite web|title=10 Bizarre Unidentified Body Cases|url=http://www.alistaday.com/10-bizarre-unidentified-body-cases/|accessdate=5 September 2014|date=7 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006070228/http://www.alistaday.com/10-bizarre-unidentified-body-cases/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=namus>{{cite web|title=Case Report \u2013 NamUs UP # 6095|url=https://identifyus.org/en/cases/6095|website=identifyus.org|publisher=[[National Missing and Unidentified Persons System]]|accessdate=5 September 2014|date=23 October 2009}}</ref>\n|No / Accident\n|-\n|1995\n|Eefje Lambrecks and An Marchal\n|19 (Lambrecks)<br>17 (Marchal)\n|Eefje Lambrecks and An Marchal, from [[Hasselt]], Belgium, were on holiday on the Flemish coast with a group of friends when they disappeared on the night of 22\u201323 August 1995. The pair took a tram to [[Blankenberge]] where they attended a hypnosis show, and did not return to their holiday home in [[Westende]]. On 3 September 1996, their bodies were found buried in the garden of a house in [[Jumet]]. [[Marc Dutroux]] and his accomplice Michel Leli\u00e8vre had kidnapped the teenagers and brought them to Dutroux's house in [[Marcinelle]]. After being kidnapped, Lambrecks and Marchal had been buried alive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lalibre.be/archive/an-et-eefje-jusqu-au-bout-de-l-horreur-51b88269e4b0de6db9a9d83b|title=An et Eefje, jusqu'au bout de l'horreur|first=La|last=Libre.be|date=9 February 2004|website=www.lalibre.be}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-08-27\"|1995\n|[[Madalyn Murray O'Hair]]\n|76\n|Madalyn Murray O'Hair, an American activist, founder of [[American Atheists]], and the organization's president from 1963 to 1986, disappeared on 27 August 1995,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local/article/true-crime-SA-kidnapping-murder-Madalyn-OHair-11017782.php|title=The true story behind the San Antonio kidnapping & murder of 'The Most Hated Woman in America'|work=San Antonio Express-News|access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref> and was found dead in 2001.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/03/16/us/bodies-identified-as-those-of-missing-atheist-and-kin.html|title=Bodies Identified as Those of Missing Atheist and Kin|last=Milloy|first=Ross E.|date=16 March 2001|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-09-11\"|1995\n|[[Jimmy Ryce]]\n|9\n|Jimmy Ryce, a child who was abducted on 11 September 1995, and was raped and killed by Juan Carlos Chavez in [[Redland, Florida]], and his body was found three months later near Chavez's trailer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/man-who-raped-killed-florida-boy-jimmy-ryce-in-1995-to-be-executed/|title=Man executed for 1995 rape, murder of Fla. boy|access-date=2017-09-09|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-10-06\"|1995\n|[[Killing of Nicole van den Hurk|Nicole van den Hurk]]\n|15\n|Nicole van den Hurk disappeared on her way to work in [[Eindhoven]], in the Dutch province of [[North Brabant]] on 6 October 1995, and was found dead on 22 November 1995, in the woods between the towns of [[Mierlo]] and [[Lierop]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nu.nl/dvn/4354196/moet-weten-zaak-nicole-van-hurk.html|title=Dit moet je weten over de zaak-Nicole van den Hurk {{!}} NU \u2013 Het laatste nieuws het eerst op NU.nl|website=www.nu.nl|access-date=2017-08-25}}</ref>\n|No / Manslaughter\n|-\n|1995\n|Bernard Weinstein\n|43\n|Bernard Weinstein, a Frenchman living in Belgium, was last seen alive in mid-November 1995. His body was found buried in the garden of a house in [[Sars-la-Buissi\u00e8re]] on 17 August 1996. Weinstein had been sought by police since he and [[Marc Dutroux]] kidnapped three people, one of whom had escaped and alerted the police. To stop Weinstein from informing on him, Dutroux kidnapped Weinstein and killed him by burying him alive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhnet.be/archive/bernard-weinstein-torture-avec-des-colliers-de-serrage-51b82fa2e4b0de6db9a061bc|title=Bernard Weinstein tortur\u00e9 avec des colliers de serrage|date=11 March 2004|website=www.dhnet.be}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-12-22\"|1995\n|[[Murder of Barbara Barnes|Barbara Barnes]]\n|13\n|Barbara Barnes, an American schoolgirl who was kidnapped on 7 December 1995, while walking to school, and her body was found on 22 February 1996 in [[Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ovcoldcasessummary.blogspot.ca/|title=All Cases Summary|website=ovcoldcasessummary.ca|access-date=2017-07-16}}</ref> People have speculated that her uncle may have been responsible for her death, but others believe that the crime was committed by someone local.<ref name=\"swaint who\">{{cite book|last=Swaint|first=Jack|title=Who killed--? Pittsburgh, PA|date=10 July 2007|publisher=Rooftop Pub.|location=Bloomington, IN|isbn=978-1600080401|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=c4pUohXVD9oC&pg=PA21&lpg=PA21&dq=barbara+barnes+murdered#v=onepage&q=barbara%20barnes%20murdered|accessdate=20 May 2014|chapter=Who Killed 13-Year-Old Barbara Ann Barnes?}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-12-29\"|1995\n|[[Murder of C\u00e9line Figard|C\u00e9line Figard]]\n|19\n|C\u00e9line Figard, a French woman who while visiting the United Kingdom disappeared on 19 December 1995, and was found dead on 29 December 1995.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/fears-grow-for-celine-after-body-is-found-1527720.html|title=Fears grow for Celine after body is found|date=30 December 1995|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-12-31\"|1995\n|[[Justina Morales]]\n|8\n|Justina Morales, an American girl from the [[Bedford-Stuyvesant]] section of [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, New York]], who was killed by her mother's boyfriend, Luis Santiago, on 31 December 1995. Her disappearance went unnoticed for 15 months. In 1997, Santiago was convicted for the murder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/12/23/nyregion/metro-news-briefs-new-york-killer-of-girl-8-gets-up-to-19-years-in-prison.html|title=METRO NEWS BRIEFS: NEW YORK; Killer of Girl, 8, Gets Up to 19 Years in Prison|date=23 December 1997|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-07-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Morales' body has not been found.\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|1996\n|[[Sabine Dardenne]]\n|12\n|Dardenne was kidnapped in [[Tournai]], Belgium, by [[Marc Dutroux]] and Michel Leli\u00e8vre as she cycled to school on 28 May 1996. When Dutroux and Leli\u00e8vre were arrested in August after kidnapping 14-year-old Laetitia Delhez, police raided Dutroux's home on 15 August and found both girls in the basement.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lalibre.be/archive/sabine-et-laetitia-la-fin-d-un-cauchemar-51b88289e4b0de6db9a9e19f|title=Sabine et Laetitia, la fin d'un cauchemar|first=La|last=Libre.be|date=10 February 2004|website=www.lalibre.be}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-02-10\"|1996\n|[[Tanya Nicole Kach]]\n|14\n|Tanya Nicole Kach, a student at the [[Cornell Middle School]] in McKeesport, Pennsylvania, was ki