</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-08-09\"|1996\n|Laetitia Delhez\n|14\n|Delhez was kidnapped by [[Marc Dutroux]] and Michel Leli\u00e8vre as she walked home from a swimming pool in [[Bertrix]], Belgium, on 9 August 1996. An eyewitness who was present at the scene of the kidnapping was able to tell the police part of Dutroux's van's numberplate. After Dutroux and Leli\u00e8vre confessed to kidnapping Delhez, police raided Dutroux's home on 15 August and found Delhez and [[Sabine Dardenne]] in the basement.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-09-27\"|1996\n|[[Murder of Karyn Hearn Slover|Karyn Hearn Slover]]\n|23\n|Karyn Hearn Slover disappeared on 27 September 1996 in [[Decatur, Illinois]], shortly after leaving her job at the Decatur ''[[Herald & Review]]'', and her dismembered body was discovered wrapped in plastic bags sealed with duct tape in [[Lake Shelbyville]] on 1 October 1996.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://herald-review.com/news/local/ruling-in-karyn-slover-murder-case-narrows-options-for-further/article_bcbef0b4-ddb5-11e0-9e28-001cc4c002e0.html|title=Ruling in Karyn Slover murder case narrows options for further appeals|last=Writer|first=HUEY FREEMAN \u2013 H&R Staff|work=Herald-Review.com|access-date=2017-09-18|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-10-01\"|1996\n|[[Abduction of Jakub Fiszman|Jakub Fiszman]]\n|39\n|Jakub Fiszman, a millionaire German businessman from [[Frankfurt am Main]], who disappeared in [[Eschborn|Eschborn, Germany]], on 1 October 1996, and his body was found on 19 October 1996 in the [[Taunus]] mountains, after a massive search operation involving some 500 police officers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archiv.rhein-zeitung.de/on/97/10/04/topnews/fiszchro.html|title=Chronologie: Die Entf\u00fchrung und Ermordung Jakub Fiszmans|website=archiv.rhein-zeitung.de|access-date=2017-09-12}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-10-03\"|1996\n|[[Murder of April Lacy|April Lacy]]\n|14\n|April Lacy, a girl from [[Oklahoma City]], Oklahoma, who disappeared on 3 October 1996, and was found dead on 8 October 1996 in [[Decatur, Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/news/nation-world/article/Prostitutes-grim-lives-end-violently-on-highway-1562282.php|title=Prostitutes' grim lives end violently on highway|work=Houston Chronicle|access-date=2017-09-23}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-02-09\"|1997\n|[[Murder of Amber Creek|Amber Creek]]\n|14\n|Amber Creek, a girl from [[Palatine, Illinois]] ran away from a youth shelter in January 1997, and was found dead on 9 February 1997, and was not identified until a year later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20140416/news/140418763/|title=Judge orders Eaton held over for trial in Amber Creek slaying|last=Graham|first=Doug T.|work=Daily Herald|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-06-28\"|1997\n|[[Gary DeVore]]\n|55\n|Gary DeVore, a Hollywood screenwriter best known for the movie ''[[Raw Deal (1986 film)|Raw Deal]]'', who disappeared on 28 June 1997, and a year later he and his car was discovered submerged in the [[California Aqueduct]] in [[Palmdale, California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/gq95k9/the-writer-with-no-hands-gary-devore-matthew-alford|title=The Mystery of the Dead Hollywood Screenwriter Whose Hands Were Never Found|website=Vice|language=en-uk|access-date=2017-09-17}}</ref>\n|No\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-11-07\"|1997\n|William Earl Moldt\n|40\n|William Moldt somehow drove his car unnoticed into the canal in the Grand Isles neighbohood of [[Lake Worth, Florida]] on 7 November 1997. His car was spotted by a man looking at a Google Earth image in late August, 2019 and his remains were recovered from the canal on 28 August of that year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Phillips Doug and Lois K. Solomon |first1=Doug and Lois K. Solomon |title=Google Earth uncovers car in p