 in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2003/apr/11/australia|title=Alleged Australian murder victim found alive|last=Staff|date=11 April 2003|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-06-13|last2=agencies|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1998-01-01\"|1998\n|[[Scott Watson#Disappearance of Smart and Hope|Ben Smart]]\n|21\n|rowspan=\"2\" |Ben Smart and Olivia Hope, [[New Zealanders|New Zealand]] party goers last seen in the early hours of 1 January 1998, who disappeared in mysterious circumstances in the [[Marlborough Sounds]]. [[Scott Watson]] was arrested for and convicted of their murder, but the verdict remains controversial and no trace of Smart or Hope has ever been discovered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crime.co.nz/c-files.aspx?ID=200 |title=crime.co.nz |publisher=Crime.co.nz |date= |accessdate=2016-10-21}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|No / Murdered\n|-\n|[[Scott Watson#Disappearance of Smart and Hope|Olivia Hope]]\n|17\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1998-06-01\"|1998\n|[[Dimitris Liantinis]]\n|55\n|Dimitris Liantinis, a [[Greeks|Greek]] philosopher and professor at the [[University of Athens]] who disappeared on 1 June 1998. In July 2005 human bones were found in the area of the mountain Taygetos; forensic examinations verified that it was the body of Liantinis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.filosofia.gr/liantinis.html|title=\u039b\u03b9\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u2013 \u0392\u03b9\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc|website=www.filosofia.gr|access-date=2017-07-12}}</ref> No lethal substances were found to determine the cause of death.\n|No\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1998-07-10\"|1998\n|[[Abduction of Kamiyah Mobley|Kamiyah Mobley]]\n|< 1\n|Kamiyah Mobley, was abducted on 10 July 1998 shortly after her birth and was recovered 18 years later after having been raised by her alleged abductor.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/13/us/abducted-newborn-found-alive-18-years-later/index.html|title=Newborn abducted from hospital found alive 18 years later, sheriff says|first=Ray|last=Sanchez|publisher=CNN|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1998-12-31\"|1998\n|[[Kirsty Bentley]]\n|15\n|Bentley, a teenage girl in [[Ashburton, New Zealand]], disappeared on 31 December 1998 while walking her family dog in the afternoon. After an extensive search lasting two weeks, her body was found in dense [[scrubland|scrub]] approximately 40&nbsp;km away.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/crime/104330963/work-and-income-double-murderer-interviewed-over-kirsty-bentley-cold-case.html|title=Work and Income double murderer interviewed over Kirsty Bentley cold case|website=Stuff|language=en|access-date=29 October 2018}}</ref> [[New Zealand Police|Police]] consider the case to be a homicide, and it remains one of the highest-profile cold cases in New Zealand. Her killer has never been identified.\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1999-09-09\"|1999\n|[[Murder of Girly Chew Hossencofft|Girly Chew Hossencofft]]\n|36\n|Girly Chew Hossencofft, a [[Malaysians|Malaysian]]-born woman who disappeared on 9 September 1999 in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]]. The investigation into the murder of Girly Chew revealed a [[conspiracy theory]] involving reptilian queens, [[UFOs]] and reports of [[cannibalism]].<ref name=\"Reptilian\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2002-09-26/justice/ctv.henning.trial_1_murder-trial-blood-grand-jury?_s=PM:LAW | work=CNN | title=Novelist's murder trial set to open in North Carolina | date=June 27, 2003}}</ref><ref name=\"Cannibal\">{{Cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2003-01-07/justice/ctv.henning.trial_1_prosecutor-claims-flesh-nurse-practitioners?_s=PM:LAW | work=CNN | title=New Yorker to argue he never meant to kill billionaire banker, nurse | date=April 9, 2002}}</ref> Girly Chew's husband Diazien Hossencofft and his girlfriend Linda Henning were convicted of her murder.<ref name=\"Charley\">{{cite news|url=http://charleyproject.org/case/girly-chew-hossencofft|title=Girly Chew Hossencofft|accessdate=12 June 2014|date=12 October 2004|publisher=The Charley Project}}</ref> Girly's body has never been found.<ref name=\"Cannibal\"/><ref name=\"Vanceholmes\">{{cite news|url=http://www.vanceholmes.com/court/trial_hossencofft.html|title=Alien Love Queen: Desert Murder Mystery|website=poeticjustice.com|year=2013}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1999-11-20\"|1999\n|Jorge Matute Johns ([[:es:Caso Matute Johns|es]])\n|23\n|Jorge Matute, a [[Chile|Chilean]] forestry student who disappeared on 20 November 1999 in a discotheque near [[Concepci\u00f3n, Chile|Concepci\u00f3n]]. In February 2004 human bones were found in the road to [[Santa Juana, Chile|Santa Juana]]; forensic examinations verified that it was the remains of Matute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias/site/artic/20050428/pags/20050428113059.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050429045436/http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias/site/artic/20050428/pags/20050428113059.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 April 2005 | work=La Naci\u00f3n | title=Restos de Jorge Matute Johns llegaron a Concepci\u00f3n ''(in Spanish)''| date=April 28, 2005}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|}\n\n==2000s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"isoDate\"|Date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Person(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Age\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Circumstances\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Found alive / cause of death\n!Time spent missing or unconfirmed\n|-\n|2000\n|C\u00e9line Saison\n|18\n|18-year-old student C\u00e9line Saison failed to return home from school in [[Charleville-M\u00e9zi\u00e8res]] on 16 May 2000. On 22 July that year, her remains were found in a forest in [[Vresse-sur-Semois]]. In 2004, [[Michel Fourniret]] admitted to kidnapping and killing her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/actualites/2008/04/24/01001-20080424ARTFIG00006-fourniret-le-face-a-faceavec-le-pere-de-celine.php|title=Fourniret : le face-\u00e0-faceavec le p\u00e8re de C\u00e9line|date=24 April 2008|website=FIGARO}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|2 months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2000-05-28\"|2000\n|[[Murder of Keith William Allan|Keith Allan]]\n|data-sort-value=\"053\"|53 or 54\n|Allan, an Australian solicitor, was murdered on 28 May 2000 in a [[contract killing]].<ref name=age-anatomy>{{cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/07/30/1091080431940.html |title=Anatomy of a suburban hit|date=31 July 2004 |work=The Age |accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref> The whereabouts of his body is unknown.<ref>Emily Webb (2014), ''Murder in Suburbia: Disturbing stories from Australia's dark heart'', The Five Mile Press, Scoresby, Victoria, p.99 {{ISBN|9781743465288}}</ref> Three men were charged with killing him and three trials took place. The second trial in 2006 resulted in a [[hung jury]]. In 2007, all three were again found guilty and were sentenced to terms ranging from twenty three and a half years to nineteen years.<ref>{{cite AustLII|VSC|289|2007|litigants=R v Cavkic, Athanasi & Clarke |date=16 August 2007 |courtname=auto}}.</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|Not found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2000-06-27|2000\n|[[Death of Molly Bish|Molly Bish]]\n|data-sort-value=\"016\"|16\n|Molly disappeared while working as a lifeguard in her hometown of [[Warren, Massachusetts]] on 27 June 2000. Her remains were found around five miles from her home in neighboring [[Hampden County, Massachusetts|Hampden County]].\n|No / Murdered\n|3 Years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2000-09-16|2000\n|[[Georgiy Gongadze]]\n|data-sort-value=\"031\"|31\n|A [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] politician and [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] journalist and film director who disappeared on 16 September 2000, and was found dead on 3 November 2000 in a forest in the [[Taraschanskyi Raion]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.article19.org/resources.php/resource/1619/en/inter