001/SHOWBIZ/Music/12/17/bigcountry/index.html|title=CNN.com \u2013 Big Country star found dead \u2013 December 17, 2001|website=www.cnn.com|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>\n|No / Suicide\n|20 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2002-01-01|2002\n|[[Alicia Kozakiewicz]]\n|data-sort-value=\"013\"|13\n|[[Child abduction|Abducted]] from [[Pittsburgh|Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]] on 1 January 2002 by 38-year-old Scott Tyree, with whom she had chatted online, believing he was a boy of her own age. Kozakiewicz was rescued four days later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://old.post-gazette.com/regionstate/20020105missingp1.asp|title=Missing teen found safe but tied up in Virginia townhouse|website=old.post-gazette.com|access-date=2017-09-15}}</ref> She went on to become a television personality and [[internet safety]] and [[missing person]]s [[Child protection|advocate]], and the founder of the Alicia Project.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/archive/abducted-enslaved-and-now-talking-about-it-vol-67-no-15/|title=Abducted, Enslaved\u2014and Now Talking About It \u2013 Vol. 67 No. 15|date=16 April 2007|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2017-09-15|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|4 days\n|-\n|2002\n|[[Murder of Milly Dowler|Amanda Dowler]]\n|13\n|Amanda Dowler, known as Milly, disappeared in [[Walton-on-Thames]] while on her way home from school on 21 March 2002. On 18 September that year, mushroom pickers found her remains in a [[Hampshire]] forest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/1947954.stm|title=Timeline: Milly Dowler|date=20 September 2002|via=news.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|6 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2002-06-05|2002\n|[[Kidnapping of Elizabeth Smart|Elizabeth Smart]]\n|data-sort-value=\"014\"|14\n|Smart was kidnapped from her bedroom on 5 June 2002, and was found to be alive when police officers rescued her nine months later on 12 March 2003 in [[Sandy, Utah]], about 18 miles from her home.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2003/03/12/elizabeth-smart-found-alive-in-utah.html|title=Elizabeth Smart Found Alive in Utah|date=12 March 2003|work=Fox News|access-date=2017-06-12|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|9 Months\n|-\n|2003\n|[[Murder of Logan Tucker|Logan Tucker]]\n|6\n|Tucker was a 6 year old American boy<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oklahoman.com/news/looking-for-logan-tucker|title=Special Series: Looking For Logan Tucker {{!}} NewsOK|website=Oklahoman.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref> who disappeared on 23 June 2002 became the victim of a murder where [[Murder conviction without a body|no body was found]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/missing-children-where-are-they/|title=Missing Children: Where are They?|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref> His mother Katherine Rutan was convicted of [[first-degree murder]] in September 2007, and the jury recommended a sentence of life in prison without the possibility of parole.<ref>{{cite news|title=Why jury said mom killed boy|url=http://newsok.com/article/3115062|accessdate=17 April 2016|newspaper=The Daily Oklahoman|date=1 September 2007}}</ref> Rutan was formally sentenced to life without parole in October 2007.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mom sits emotionless as judge locks her up for life|url=http://newsok.com/mom-sits-emotionless-as-judge-locks-her-up-for-life/article/3144144|accessdate=17 April 2015|newspaper=The Daily Oklahoman|date=10 October 2007}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2002-08-15\" |2002\n|[[Murder of Jon-Niece Jones|Jon-Niece Jones]]\n| data-sort-value=\"009\" |9\n|An American girl who disappeared on 15 August 2002 and whose unidentified [[skeleton|skeletal remains]] were found on 18 March 2005 near the gated forest of [[New Jersey]]'s [[Six Flags Great Adventure]] [[theme park]], by a deer [[hunter]].<ref name=\"remains\" /><ref name=\"three\">{{cite news|title=Three New Yorkers Charged In 'Baby Bones' Case|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2012/10/10/nj-prosecutors-3-nyers-charged-in-baby-bones-case/|accessdate=21 July 2015|work=CBS New York|agency=CBS|date=10 October 2012}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|2 1/2 Years\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2002-10-09\" |2002\n|[[Murder of Amanda Zhao|Amanda Zhao]]\n| data-sort-value=\"021\" |21\n|An international student in [[Vancouver|Vancouver, British Columbia]], who disappeared on 9 October 2002, and her body was found in a suitcase by hikers near [[Stave Lake]] on 20 October 2002.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/visiting-parents-demand-justice-in-zhao-s-slaying-6-years-ago-1.706069|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011154642/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/visiting-parents-demand-justice-in-zhao-s-slaying-6-years-ago-1.706069|url-status=dead|archive-date=2008-10-11|title=Visiting parents demand justice in Zhao's slaying 6 years ago|date=11 October 2008|access-date=2017-09-20}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|11 Days\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2002-12-24\" |2002\n|[[Laci Peterson]]\n| data-sort-value=\"027\" |27\n|Laci Peterson disappeared while 8 months pregnant with her first child on 24 December 2002. On 13 April 2003, a couple walking their dog discovered her body. Peterson's husband was found guilty of murdering her.\n|No / Murdered\n|5 Months\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2003-04-21\" |2003\n|[[Ariel Castro kidnappings#Amanda Berry|Amanda Berry]]\n| data-sort-value=\"016\" |16\n|Berry disappeared on 21 April 2003, the day before her 17th birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-22433057 |title=Profile: Amanda Berry, Georgina DeJesus and Michele Knight |date=7 May 2013 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=13 May 2013}}</ref> She was walking home from her job at [[Burger King]]. During captivity, Berry gave birth to a daughter. Just over 10 years later, on 6 May 2013, Berry escaped along with Michelle Knight, Gina DeJesus and Berry's daughter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespec.com/news-story/2555271-