rate]], who confessed to murdering the victim in 2016. Her remains were found in March 2007 but not identified.  Lowrey was identified by the [[DNA Doe Project]] in June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Minden woman, missing since 2006, identified as victim of serial killer {{!}} Minden Press-Herald |url=https://press-herald.com/minden-woman-missing-since-2006-identified-as-victim-of-serial-killer/ |accessdate=5 June 2019 |work=press-herald.com |date=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|10 Months\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2006-06-10\" |2006\n|[[Murder of Nathalie Mahy and Stacy Lemmens|Nathalie Mahy and Stacy Lemmens]]\n| data-sort-value=\"11 and 7\" |11 and 7\n|[[Murder of Nathalie Mahy and Stacy Lemmens|Nathalie Mahy and Stacy Lemmens]] were two [[Belgian]] stepsisters, who disappeared in the city of [[Li\u00e8ge]] on 10 June 2006 and were found murdered on 28 June 2006.<ref>[http://edition.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/europe/06/28/belgium.children/index.html Bodies of missing girls found], CNN</ref> On 10 June 2008, Abdallah Ait Oud was found guilty by a jury of kidnapping, rape and murder of the children, and sentenced to life imprisonment (which, under the Belgian law, is most of the time not fully served in prison but later on changed into a [[suspended sentence]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blikopdewereld.nl/rechtspraak/70-levenslange-gevangenisstraf/536-hoe-lang-duurt-levenslange-gevangenisstraf-in-belgie.html|title=Invuloefening Feniks Hoofdstuk 1 Van vuistbijl tot sikkel \u2013 Blik op de Wereld|website=www.blikopdewereld.nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lesoir.be/actualite/belgique/assises-de-liege-l-assassin-2008-06-10-604850.shtml|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080613024343/http://www.lesoir.be/actualite/belgique/assises-de-liege-l-assassin-2008-06-10-604850.shtml|url-status=dead|title=\"Ait Oud, reconnu coupable, s'effondre\" (lesoir.be)|archivedate=13 June 2008}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lesoir.be/actualite/belgique/deliberation-su