becke/luebbecke/4974302_Fernsehsender-sucht-den-Moerder-von-Frauke-Liebs.html|title=Fernsehsender sucht den M\u00f6rder von Frauke Liebs|last=POLLMEIER|first=VON UWE|work=L\u00fcbbecke|access-date=2017-08-16|language=de}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|14 Weeks\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2006-07-16\" |2006\n|[[Murder of Destiny Norton|Destiny Norton]]\n| data-sort-value=\"005\" |5\n|Disappeared on 16 July 2006 from [[Salt Lake City|Salt Lake City, Utah]]. Her body was found on 24 July 2006, less than 100 feet from her home in the basement of her neighbor, Craig Roger Gregerson.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ksl.com/article/380101/destiny-norton-found-dead-suspect-arrested|title=Destiny Norton Found Dead, Suspect Arrested|website=www.ksl.com}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|8 Days\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2006-10-07\" |2006\n|[[Murder of Michelle Gardner-Quinn|Michelle Gardner-Quinn]]\n| data-sort-value=\"021\" |21\n|An undergraduate at the [[University of Vermont]], who was kidnapped on 7 October 2006. Her body was found along a road in the neighboring town of [[Richmond, Vermont|Richmond]] on 13 October 2006.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/vt-slay-suspect-has-a-sordid-past/|title=Vt. Slay Suspect Has A Sordid Past|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|6 Days\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2007-02-21\" |2007\n|[[Murder of Erika Hill|Erika Hill]]\n| data-sort-value=\"015\" |15\n|Erika was an [[United States|American]] 15-year-old girl who was murdered in [[Fitchburg, Wisconsin]], in February 2007. Hill's damaged body was found in [[Gary, Indiana]] on February 26, and her identity was not discovered until 2015. Taylin Hill, her adoptive mother, was charged with [[reckless homicide]] after Hill's identification, and later pleaded guilty to reduced charges for which she was sentenced to 20 years imprisonment.  Her body was first taken to Chicago and burned, then five days later it was moved to [[Gary, Indiana]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://host.madiso