 of Libya|Libyan]] political figure, who disappeared in August 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-20016076|title=Libya: Confusion at fate of Gaddafi aide Moussa Ibrahim|date=21 October 2012|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-08-22|language=en-GB}}</ref> In October 2014, he was discovered in, and later deported from, [[Egypt]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/31/egypt-gaddafi-spokesman-idUSL5N0SQ43O20141031|title=WebCite query result|website=www.webcitation.org|language=en|access-date=2017-08-29|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6TwKvuAY4?url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/31/egypt-gaddafi-spokesman-idUSL5N0SQ43O20141031|archivedate=8 November 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|3 Years 2 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2011-11-01\"|2011\n|[[Death of Erica Parsons|Erica Parsons]]\n|data-sort-value=\"013\"|13\n|Last seen in [[North Carolina]] by persons outside her family in November 2011. In 2016, her remains were found in 2016 in a shallow grave near her adoptive grandmother's house in an adjacent portion of [[South Carolina]]. It is strongly believed that she was murdered by her own adoptive parents, who allegedly abused her.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/erica-parsons-remains-found-of-north-carolina-girl-who-went-missing-in-2011-officials-say/|title=Remains found of N.C. girl who went missing in 2011, officials say|access-date=2017-03-25|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|4 Years 10 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2012-03-01\"|2012\n|[[Gemma McCluskie]]\n|data-sort-value=\"029\"|29\n|A British television actress who disappeared from her home in [[East (London sub region)|East London]] on 1 March 2012. Her dismembered body was discovered on 6 March 2012 in the [[Regent's Canal]]. Her brother, Tony McCluskie was charged and found guilty of her murder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/mar/10/gemma-mccluskie-eastender-actor-murder-brother-charged|titl