30/april-jones-murder-final-hours|title=April Jones murder: how detectives pieced together her final hours|last=Morris|first=Steven|date=30 May 2013|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-08-06|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> after forensic evidence was found in his car and home but her body has never been found.\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2012-12-20\"|2012\n|[[Tokbergen Abiyev]]\n|data-sort-value=\"005\"|unknown\n|A [[Kazakhs|Kazakh]] journalist who went missing on 20 December 2012, just hours after he announced to the Kazakh media that he had a sensational news report about to be published.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpj.org/2012/12/journalist-press-club-founder-disappears-in-kazakh.php|title=Journalist, press club founder disappears in Kazakhstan|publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists|date=27 December 2012|accessdate=28 December 2012}}</ref> Abiyev reappeared on 4 January 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/missing-journalist-reappears-freedom-information-doesnt|title=\"Missing\" journalist reappears, but freedom of information doesn't {{!}} Reporters without borders|website=RSF|language=fr-FR|access-date=2017-08-11}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|2 Weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2013-04-01\"|2013\n|[[Murder of Glory Chau and Moon Siu|Glory Chau Wing-ki and Moon Siu Yuet-yee]]\n|data-sort-value=\"63 and 65\"|63 and 65\n|[[Murder of Glory Chau and Moon Siu|Glory Chau Wing-ki and Moon Siu Yuet-yee]] were an elderly couple murdered in [[Hong Kong]], presumably on 1 March 2013. Their youngest son Henry Chau Hoi-leung and his friend Angus Tse Chun-kei were indicted for the murder, which they initially denied being involved in.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/realtime/news/20130315/51300595|title=\u3010\u9006\u5b50\u5f12\u7236\u6bcd\u3011 \u9000\u4f11\u592b\u5a66\u6158\u906d\u9006\u5b50\u8b00\u8ca1\u5bb3\u547d \u2013 \u5373\u6642\u65b0\u805e \u2013 \u8981\u805e \u2013 20130315|work=Apple Daily \u860b\u679c\u65e5\u5831|acce