=Christine|title=Court documents reveal disturbing new information in Jessica Heeringa case|url=http://wwmt.com/news/local/court-documents-reveal-disturbing-new-information-in-jessica-heeringa-case|accessdate=5 January 2017|work=WWMT}}</ref> Willis was found guilty of Heeringa's kidnapping and murder on 16 May 2018.<ref>[http://www.mlive.com/news/muskegon/index.ssf/2018/05/jeffrey_willis_found_guilty_of.html Jeffrey Willis found guilty of kidnapping, murdering Jessica Heeringa] ''The Muskegon Chronicle'' via MLive.com, May 16, 2018</ref> He received a life sentence without parole a month later.<ref>[http://www.woodtv.com/news/jeffrey-willis-investigation/willis-claims-innocence-at-heeringa-murder-sentence/1230498914 Willis claims innocence at Heeringa murder sentence] WOOD-TV, June 18, 2018</ref> On 27 November 2017, Bluhm pleaded no contest to being an accessory after the fact for helping Willis dispose of Heeringa's body and was sentenced on 9 January 2018 to time served, plus five years probation and to wear a GPS tether for at least a year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin Bluhm walks free for his role in Jessica Heeringa's murder|url=http://www.mlive.com/news/muskegon/index.ssf/2018/01/kevin_bluhm_walks_free_for_his.html|website=MLive.com|accessdate=15 March 2018}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2013-05-13\"|2013\n|[[Ingrid Visser (volleyball)|Ingrid Visser]] and [[Ingrid Visser (volleyball)|Lodewijk Severein]]\n|data-sort-value=\"035 and 035\"|35 and 35\n|Visser and her boyfriend Lodewijk Severein disappeared on 13 May 2013 shortly after checking into a hotel in the city of Murcia, Spain. Visser was a member of the [[Netherlands women's national volleyball team]]. Their bodies were found in a shallow grave in a lemon grove on 27 May. The pair had been abducted, tortured and killed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/511542-severein-met-veel-geweld-vermoord.html|title=Severein met veel geweld vermoord|access-date=2017-12-22|language