llowknife, Northwest Territories]], Canada. Her disappearance was not noted until three days later, when she had failed to check out of her hotel and the staff found her luggage, all packed, in her room. An intense search both by the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) and concerned local residents over the next few days was called off after a week when the RCMP announced that their investigation had led them to conclude that she came to Yellowknife with the intent to disappear into the wilderness (although she had bought a return ticket to Japan and souvenirs).<ref>{{cite news|last=O'Connor|first=Joe|title=RCMP believes Japanese psychiatrist had suicidal plan to disappear into wilderness outside Yellowknife|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/news/canada/rcmp-believe-missing-japanese-psychiatrist-had-suicidal-plan-to-disappear-into-wilderness-outside-yellowknife|newspaper=[[National Post]]|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> Ten months later a hunter discovered some of her personal effects along with human remains in [[the bush]] off the highway; on April 14, 2016, those remains were positively identified as Yoshikubo's.<ref>{{cite news|title=DNA confirms remains found in 2015 belong to Atsumi Yoshikubo, missing Japanese tourist|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/north/atsumi-yoshikubo-dna-confirms-id-human-remains-1.3536268|newspaper=CBC|date=14 April 2016|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n|No\n|10 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-06-16|2014\n|[[Disappearance of Charles Bothuell V|Charles Bothuell V]]\n|data-sort-value=\"012\"|12\n|An American boy from [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]], reported missing by his father in June 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2015/02/20/parents-boy-held-basement-charged-torture/23779195/|title=Parents of boy held in basement charged with torture|work=USA TODAY|access-date=2017-08-09|language=en}}</ref> When a search was conducted to find him, he was found alive eleven days la