der|whole life sentence]] in October 2016.<ref name=\"whole\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-37565626|title=Life sentence for ex-Easteners' actress Sian Blake killer|work=[[BBC News]]|date=5 October 2016|accessdate=5 October 2016}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|3 Weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2015-10-17\"|2015\n|[[Gui Minhai]]\n|data-sort-value=\"051\"|51\n|The Chinese-born Swedish scholar and book publisher went missing in [[Thailand]] on 17 October 2015. He was the second of five book publishers to go missing around the same time. It was thought that he had been abducted by Chinese authorities and taken to China in relation to a fatal hit and run car accident in 2003 when he had been driving while intoxicated, as he appeared on Chinese television and made an apparent confession a few months after disappearing. Complaints about alleged Chinese abduction reached high political levels in Britain and the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/05/25/asia/hong-kong-bookseller-gui-minhai-us-cecc/index.html|title=HK bookseller's daughter: My father was abducted|first=James |last=Griffiths|work=CNN|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref> Later, Gui was charged in China with \"illegal business operations\".\n|Yes\n|Several Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2016-04-01\"|2016\n|[[Helen Bailey]]\n|data-sort-value=\"051\"|51\n|The British writer of children's and teenage fiction was reported missing after allegedly taking her dog for a walk in [[Royston, Hertfordshire]], England, in April 2016. No trace of her was found initially, but in July 2016 her remains (and the dogs) were found in a cesspit under the garage of her home and her partner was charged with her murder.<ref name=bbc160716>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-36814157 \"Helen Bailey death: Partner charged with murdering children's author\", ''BBC News'', 16 July 2016]. Retrieved 16 July 2016</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|3 Months\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Murder of Sierah Joughin|Sierah Joughin]]\n|20\