uthor2=Pierre Meilhan |author3=Ella Hurworth|website=CNN|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2017-08-01\" |2017\n|[[Death of Santiago Maldonado|Santiago Maldonado]]\n|data-sort-value=\"027\"|27\n|An [[Argentine]] craftsman and tattoo artist from the town of [[Veinticinco de Mayo, Buenos Aires|Veinticinco de Mayo]], [[province of Buenos Aires]], who was reported missing after a demonstration in Chubut on 1 August 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias-america-latina-40868877|title=Qui\u00e9n es Santiago Maldonado, el joven cuya desaparici\u00f3n tiene en vilo a Argentina|last=Smink|first=Veronica|date=8 August 2017|work=BBC Mundo|access-date=2017-09-17|language=es}}</ref> His body was found three months after, drowned at [[Chubut River]]. On 21 October 2017, after a 12-hour autopsy involving 55 experts, Judge Gustavo Lleral confirmed that Maldonado's body did not have any signs of violence and the cause of death was established as death by drowning.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clarin.com/politica/caso-maldonado-lesiones-cuerpo-dijo-juez-autopsia_0_SkNyi4daW.html|title=Caso Maldonado: \"No hubo lesiones en el cuerpo\", dijo el juez tras la autopsia|date=21 October 2017|publisher=[[Clar\u00edn (Argentine newspaper)|Clar\u00edn]]|accessdate=2017-10-22|language=es}}</ref>\n|No / Drowning\n|10 Weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2017-08-11\"|2017\n|[[Murder of Kim Wall|Kim Wall]]\n|data-sort-value=\"030\"|30\n|Swedish [[freelance journalist]] Kim Wall was reported missing after failing to return from a voyage on [[Peter Madsen]]'s [[submarine]] ''[[UC3 Nautilus]]'' on 10 August 2017. Over the next three months, her severed body parts were found in [[K\u00f8ge Bay]]. In April 2018, Madsen was convicted of her murder and sentenced to [[life imprisonment]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/tidslinje-faa-overblik-over-ubaadssagen-her|title=TIDSLINJE F\u00e5 overblik over ub\u00e5dssagen her|website=DR