ers: The Bog Grave|work=Imgur|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0147\"|147 days\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" data-sort-value=\"1954-06-10\"|1954\n|Eugene Lindsey\n|45\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Father and son Eugene and Richard Lindsey, and their friend Frederick Claar, were last seen on June 12, 1954 in the [[Gasp\u00e9 Peninsula|Gasp\u00e9]] region of Quebec, where they had driven to from [[Hollidaysburg, Pennsylvania]] on a hunting trip. Eugene Lindsey's body was discovered in deep bush a month later (July 15) and those of the other two men on July 23, some 4 kilometres away. Their clothes had bullet holes in them. The discoveries led to the arrest of a prospector named [[Wilbert Coffin]] and his conviction based on circumstantial evidence. He was eventually hanged. The case is well known in Canada as the [[Coffin Affair]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070322093151/http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/features/onlineextras/news/story.html?id=5c9ac7d5-69b9-46a9-afdf-5422194f1467 Was the Wrong Man Hanged?] ''Montreal Gazette'', August 16, 2006]</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0033\"|33 days\n|-\n|Richard Lindsey\n|17\n|data-sort-value=\"0041\"|41 days\n|-\n|Frederick Claar\n|19\n|data-sort-value=\"0041\"|41 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1955\"|1955\n|[[Curtis Chillingworth]]\n|58 \n|Curtis Chillingworth was a Florida attorney and [[United States federal judge|state judge]] who disappeared from his [[Manalapan, Florida]] home in 1955. He was later discovered to have been murdered though his body was never recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biographies.net/people//en/curtis_chillingworth|title=Biography of Curtis Chillingworth|website=www.biographies.net|language=en|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0000\"|never found\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1956-12-18\"|1956\n|Barbara Grimes\n|15\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Murder of the Grimes sisters|Barbara and Patricia Grimes]] were