&pg=PA41|title=LIFE|last=Inc|first=Time|date=5 March 1965|publisher=Time Inc|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8NybAAAACAAJ|title=Among the Missing: An Anecdotal History of Missing Persons from 1800 to the Present|last=Nash|first=Jay Robert|date=1 January 1978|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9780671240059|language=en}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"2920\"|8 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1957-12-03\"|1957\n|[[Murder of Maria Ridulph|Maria Ridulph]]\n|data-sort-value=\"0007\"|7 \n|Maria Ridulph was an American girl who disappeared on 3 December 1957 from a street corner in her neighborhood in [[Sycamore, Illinois]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/11/us/maria-ridulphs-killer-gets-life-55-years-after-her-death.html|title=Maria Ridulph's Killer Gets Life 55 Years After Her Death|last=Goode|first=Erica|date=10 December 2012|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-09-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Her body was found in [[Woodbine, Illinois|Woodbine]], 100 miles from her home, on 26 April 1958.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://idnc.library.illinois.edu/cgi-bin/illinois?a=d&d=STR19580429.2.6#|title=True Republican 29 April 1958 \u2013 Illinois Digital Newspaper Collections|website=idnc.library.illinois.edu|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0144\"|144 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1958\"|1958\n|[[Ishinosuke Uwano]] \n|35 to 36\n|Ishinosuke Uwano is a former soldier in the [[Japanese Imperial Army]] who disappeared in 1958 and was found living in [[Ukraine]] in April 2006.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4916294.stm|title=Japanese WWII soldier found alive|date=18 April 2006|access-date=2017-09-12|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"17520\"|48 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1961\"|1961\n|[[Lucy Ann Johnson]] \n|25\n|Lucy Ann Johnson disappeared in 1961 from [[British Columbia]], Canada but was not reported missing by her family until 1965. In 2013 she was found alive in [[Yukon]], Canada, having started a new family after her disappearance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Missing mom found alive in Canada after more than 50 years|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2013/07/20/missing-mom-found-alive-in-canada-after-more-than-50-years/|accessdate=20 July 2013|publisher=Fox News|date=20 July 2013}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"18980\"|52 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1965\"|1965\n|[[Ajjamada B. Devaiah]] \n|32 or 33\n|Ajjamada B. Devaiah, an [[Indian Air Force]] pilot, was shot down in an [[aerial dogfight]] in 1965 over [[Pakistan]]. The Indian Air Force was unaware of what happened and declared him missing. It was revealed much later by Pakistan sources, based on a 1979 book by John Fricker, that Devayya's body was found almost intact by villagers not very far from [[Sargodha]] and buried. He was decorated posthumously in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|title=Squadron Leader Ajammada Boppaya Devayya|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/IAF/Database/4810|publisher=Bharat Rakshak|accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref>\n|No / [[Killed in action]]\n|data-sort-value=\"5110\"|14 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1967-03-16\"|1967\n|[[Alvar Larsson]]\n|13\n|Alvar Larsson was a [[Swedes|Swedish]] boy who disappeared on 16 April 1967 while going for a walk.<ref name=\"Google Translate\">{{Cite web|url=https://translate.google.ca/translate?sl=sv&u=http://29juli1965.blogspot.com/2016/05/alvar-larsson-forsvann-1967-vad-hande.html|title=Google Translate|website=translate.google.ca|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://s1033.photobucket.com/user/daCosta_arkivet/library/Ovrigt/Alvar%20Larsson%201967?sort=3&page=1|title=Alvar Larsson 1967 by daCosta_arkivet|work=Photobucket|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref> In November 1982 a human skull was found on a small island 6&nbsp;km away that was identified as belonging to Larsson.<ref name=\"Google Translate\"/>\n|No\n|data-sort-value=\"5678\"|15 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1967-12-06\"|1967\n|[[Barbara Ann Hackmann Taylor]]\n|24\n|Barbara Ann Hackmann Taylor disappeared on 6 December 1967 and was found dead near [[Georgetown, Kentucky]] on 17 May 1968.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1696&dat=19980423&id=9PEaAAAAIBAJ&pg=6796,2875583|title=Doaily News|website=news.google.com|access-date=2017-08-25}}</ref> Her unidentified body found wrapped in canvas, similar to that used for a tent, and she was dubbed \"Tent Girl\". The son-in-law of the man who discovered her body had an interest in the case and contacted her relatives after seeing a missing persons report. Barbara Taylor's remains were positively identified in 1998 following DNA testing.  \n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0163\"|163 days \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1969-11-14\"|1969\n|[[Murder of Reet Jurvetson|Reet Jurvetson]]\n|19\n|Reet Jurvetson, a [[Canadian Americans|Canadian-American]] woman disappeared on 14 November 1969 and was found murdered on 16 November 1969 in a dense bushland off [[Mulholland Drive]] in Los Angeles, California. She had been stabbed over 150 times and her body was rolled down an embankment. Jurvetson remained unidentified for 46 years until an online mortuary photograph was recognised by her family and friends.<ref name=\"could\">{{cite news|last1=Siemaszko|first1=Corky|title=Reet Jurvetson, Killed in 1969, Could Be a Manson Family Murder Victim|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/reet-jurvetson-killed-1969-could-be-manson-family-murder-victim-n564106|accessdate=7 September 2016|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=28 April 2016}}</ref> \n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"16790\"|46 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1969\"|1969\n|[[Murder of Reyna Marroquin|Reyna Marroquin]]\n|27\n|Reyna Marroquin, a pregnant [[Salvadoran]] woman, disappeared in 1969 from [[Nassau County, New York]]. Her remains were found on 2 September 1999 in the former [[Jericho, New York|Jericho]], [[New York (state)|New York]] home of Howard B. Elkins, her former boss, sealed in a drum that was stored in a crawl space. Marroquin was having an affair with Elkins and DNA test showed that Elkins was the father of the fetus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/missing-for-30-years/|title=Missing For 30 Years|access-date=2017-08-28|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://truecrimetruant.com/index.php/tag/reyna-marroquin/|title=Reyna Marroquin \u2013 True Crime Truant|website=truecrimetruant.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2000-01-22/news/0001220143_1_elkins-unborn-child-dna|title=Dna Links Suicide To Killing|work=tribunedigital-sunsentinel|access-date=2017-08-28|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"10950\"|30 years \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1970-09-24\"|1970\n|[[Jacques Verg\u00e8s]]\n|\n|Jacques Verg\u00e8s, a French-Vietnamese lawyer, left his wife [[Djamila Bouhired]] and cut off all ties with friends and family. He was last seen on 24 February 1970 until he reappeared in 1978 and refused to explain his disappearance or whereabouts during that period.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/law-obituaries/10247180/Jacques-Verges.html|title=Jacques Verg\u00e8s|work=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2017-08-12|language=en}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|data-sort-value=\"2920\"|8 years \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"1970-06-22\"|1970\n|Harvey Crewe\n|28\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Harvey and Jeannette Crewe]], a New Zealand farming couple, were reported missing from their bloodstained farmhouse at [[Pukekawa]], [[Waikato Plains|Lower Waikato]] on 22 June 1970 where their unharmed 18-month-old daughter was found in her cot. Jeannette Crewe's body was found, wrapped in a duvet and bound with copper wire, in the [[Waikato River]] on 16 August 1970 and her husband's body was retrieved upriver on 16 September 1970.<ref>\"Forensic History: Crimes, Frauds, and Scandals\" by Professor Elizabeth A Murray</ref> The initial indications from 