1 June 2018|publisher=USAToday}}</ref>\n|Yes\n| data-sort-value=\"12775\"|35 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1984-06-01\"|1984\n|[[Murder of Mark Tildesley|Mark Tildesley]]\n|data-sort-value=\"007\"|7\n|Mark Tildesley disappeared while visiting a funfair in [[Berkshire|Wokingham, Berkshire, England]] on the evening of 1 June 1984. He was lured away from the fair and his bicycle was found chained to railings nearby.<ref name=BBC570385>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/570385.stm|title=Cooke: The predatory paedophile|work=[[BBC News]]|date=17 December 1999|accessdate=22 April 2015}}</ref> In 1990 it emerged that Mark had been [[Child abduction|abducted]], drugged, [[torture]]d, [[rape]]d and [[murder]]ed by a [[London]]-based [[Pedophilia|paedophile]] [[gang]] on the night he disappeared.<ref name=BBC570385/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/paedophile-gets-life-for-killing-boy-7-at-orgy-homosexual-ring-abducted-children-and-drugged-them-for-group-sex-1559081.html|title=Paedophile gets life for killing boy, 7, at orgy: Homosexual ring abducted children and drugged them for group sex |publisher=[[The Independent]]|date=23 October 1992|accessdate=30 January 2013}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n| data-sort-value=\"0000\"|never found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1984-09-17\"|1984\n|[[Murder of Vicki Lynne Hoskinson|Vicki Lynne Hoskinson]]\n|data-sort-value=\"008\"|8\n|Vicki Lynne Hoskinson was a girl from [[Flowing Wells, Arizona]], who disappeared on 17 September 1984, while riding her bike to mail a birthday card to her aunt. Her remains were found on 12 April 1985.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://arizonaalumni.com/article/forensic-legend-our-own-backyard|title=Forensic Legend in Our Own Backyard|first=Jeff|last=Harrison|year=2015|work=Arizona Alumni Magazine|accessdate=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"0217|7 months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1984-04-06|1984\n|[[Redhead murders|Elizabeth Lamotte]]\n|17\n|Elizabeth Lamotte disappeared from [[Manchester, New Hampshire]] on 6 April 1984. Her body was discovered in Tennessee a year later but was not identified until 2018. Lamotte was possibly a victim of an unidentified serial killer.<ref>{{cite news |title=Remains of missing Manchester woman last seen in 1984 identified, possible link to string of homicides |url=https://manchesterinklink.com/remains-of-missing-manchester-woman-last-seen-in-1984-identified-possible-link-to-string-of-homicides/ |accessdate=14 November 2018 |work=Manchester Ink Link |date=14 November 2018}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"12410\"|34 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1985-01-01\"|ca. 1985\n|[[Redhead murders|Espy Pilgrim]]\n|33\n|Espy Pilgrim of North Carolina lost contact with her family sometime in the early to mid 1980s. Her body was discovered on April 1, 1985 in Kentucky but her body remained unidentified until 2018.<ref name=espy>{{cite news |title=\"Knox County Jane Doe\" positively identified 33 years later \u2013 ABC 36 News |url=https://www.wtvq.com/2018/10/01/knox-county-jane-doe-positively-identified-33-years-later/ |accessdate=1 October 2018 |work=ABC 36 News |date=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|data-sort-value=\"12045\"|33 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1986-05-12\"|1986\n|[[Wanda Jean Mays]]\n|26 \n|Wanda Jean Mays disappeared after midnight on 12 May 1986, while staying with her aunt and uncle's home near [[Guntersville Lake]], [[Alabama]]. In the morning, her aunt and uncle discovered her room empty and the window broken from the inside. In 2008, the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] confirmed that remains found at the foot of a cliff {{convert|2|mi|km}} from her relatives' home were Mays', and her death was ruled an accident.<ref>{{cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080129124545/http://www.wsbtv.com/news/15122677/detail.html |url=http://www.wsbtv.com/news/15122677/detail.html? |work=WSB-TV |location=Atlanta, Georgia |archivedate=29 January 2008 |date=23 January 20