cember 1995, while walking to school, and her body was found on 22 February 1996 in [[Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ovcoldcasessummary.blogspot.ca/|title=All Cases Summary|website=ovcoldcasessummary.ca|access-date=2017-07-16}}</ref> People have speculated that her uncle may have been responsible for her death, but others believe that the crime was committed by someone local.<ref name=\"swaint who\">{{cite book|last=Swaint|first=Jack|title=Who killed--? Pittsburgh, PA|date=10 July 2007|publisher=Rooftop Pub.|location=Bloomington, IN|isbn=978-1600080401|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=c4pUohXVD9oC&pg=PA21&lpg=PA21&dq=barbara+barnes+murdered#v=onepage&q=barbara%20barnes%20murdered|accessdate=20 May 2014|chapter=Who Killed 13-Year-Old Barbara Ann Barnes?}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-12-29\"|1995\n|[[Murder of C\u00e9line Figard|C\u00e9line Figard]]\n|19\n|C\u00e9line Figard, a French woman who while visiting the United Kingdom disappeared on 19 December 1995, and was found dead on 29 December 1995.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/fears-grow-for-celine-after-body-is-found-1527720.html|title=Fears grow for Celine after body is found|date=30 December 1995|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1995-12-31\"|1995\n|[[Justina Morales]]\n|8\n|Justina Morales, an American girl from the [[Bedford-Stuyvesant]] section of [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, New York]], who was killed by her mother's boyfriend, Luis Santiago, on 31 December 1995. Her disappearance went unnoticed for 15 months. In 1997, Santiago was convicted for the murder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/12/23/nyregion/metro-news-briefs-new-york-killer-of-girl-8-gets-up-to-19-years-in-prison.html|title=METRO NEWS BRIEFS: NEW YORK; Killer of Girl, 8, Gets Up to 19 Years in Prison|date=23 December 1997|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-07-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Morales' body has not been found.\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|1996\n|[[Sabine Dardenne]]\n|12\n|Dardenne was kidnapped in [[Tournai]], Belgium, by [[Marc Dutroux]] and Michel Leli\u00e8vre as she cycled to school on 28 May 1996. When Dutroux and Leli\u00e8vre were arrested in August after kidnapping 14-year-old Laetitia Delhez, police raided Dutroux's home on 15 August and found both girls in the basement.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lalibre.be/archive/sabine-et-laetitia-la-fin-d-un-cauchemar-51b88289e4b0de6db9a9e19f|title=Sabine et Laetitia, la fin d'un cauchemar|first=La|last=Libre.be|date=10 February 2004|website=www.lalibre.be}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-02-10\"|1996\n|[[Tanya Nicole Kach]]\n|14\n|Tanya Nicole Kach, a student at the [[Cornell Middle School]] in McKeesport, Pennsylvania, was kidnapped by school security guard Thomas Hose on 10 February 1996. In the time leading up to this event, Hose befriended Kach to earn her trust. Kach escaped on 21 March 2006, with the help of Joe Sparico, the owner of a grocery store in the neighborhood where Kach had been held captive.\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-06-09\"|1996\n|[[Murder of Melanie Hall|Melanie Hall]]\n|25\n|Melanie Hall, a British hospital clerical officer from [[Bradford on Avon]], who disappeared on 9 June 1996.<ref name=\"Tele\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/6270860/Melanie-Hall-timeline.html|title=Melanie Hall: timeline|date=8 October 2009|work=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=8 October 2009 | location=London}}</ref><ref name=\"TimelineBBC\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/bristol/8295701.stm|title=Timeline: Melanie Hall disappearance |date=7 October 2009|publisher=BBC|accessdate=8 October 2009}}</ref> On 5 October 2009 her partial remains were discovered, after a plastic bin bag containing human bones was located by a workman on the [[M5 motorway]] near [[Thornbury, South Gloucestershire|Thornbury]], South Gloucestershire. The bones, which included a pelvis, thigh bone, and human skull, were analyzed and identified as belonging to Hall.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-36468470|title=Melanie Hall murder probe: DNA evidence discovered|date=8 June 2016|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-07-26|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-06-11\"|1996\n|Ulrike Everts\n|13\n|German Ulrike Everts was last seen in a pony-drawn carriage on 11 June 1996. In July 1998, [[Ronny Rieken]], arrested for the murder of 11-year-old Christina Nytsch, confessed to killing Everts and directed police to the location where he had hidden her body.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-7940778.html|title=KRIMINALIT\u00c4T: \"Etwas ganz, ganz Schlimmes\"|date=27 July 1998|volume=31|via=Spiegel Online}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-08-09\"|1996\n|Laetitia Delhez\n|14\n|Delhez was kidnapped by [[Marc Dutroux]] and Michel Leli\u00e8vre as she walked home from a swimming pool in [[Bertrix]], Belgium, on 9 August 1996. An eyewitness who was present at the scene of the kidnapping was able to tell the police part of Dutroux's van's numberplate. After Dutroux and Leli\u00e8vre confessed to kidnapping Delhez, police raided Dutroux's home on 15 August and found Delhez and [[Sabine Dardenne]] in the basement.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-09-27\"|1996\n|[[Murder of Karyn Hearn Slover|Karyn Hearn Slover]]\n|23\n|Karyn Hearn Slover disappeared on 27 September 1996 in [[Decatur, Illinois]], shortly after leaving her job at the Decatur ''[[Herald & Review]]'', and her dismembered body was discovered wrapped in plastic bags sealed with duct tape in [[Lake Shelbyville]] on 1 October 1996.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://herald-review.com/news/local/ruling-in-karyn-slover-murder-case-narrows-options-for-further/article_bcbef0b4-ddb5-11e0-9e28-001cc4c002e0.html|title=Ruling in Karyn Slover murder case narrows options for further appeals|last=Writer|first=HUEY FREEMAN \u2013 H&R Staff|work=Herald-Review.com|access-date=2017-09-18|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-10-01\"|1996\n|[[Abduction of Jakub Fiszman|Jakub Fiszman]]\n|39\n|Jakub Fiszman, a millionaire German businessman from [[Frankfurt am Main]], who disappeared in [[Eschborn|Eschborn, Germany]], on 1 October 1996, and his body was found on 19 October 1996 in the [[Taunus]] mountains, after a massive search operation involving some 500 police officers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archiv.rhein-zeitung.de/on/97/10/04/topnews/fiszchro.html|title=Chronologie: Die Entf\u00fchrung und Ermordung Jakub Fiszmans|website=archiv.rhein-zeitung.de|access-date=2017-09-12}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1996-10-03\"|1996\n|[[Murder of April Lacy|April Lacy]]\n|14\n|April Lacy, a girl from [[Oklahoma City]], Oklahoma, who disappeared on 3 October 1996, and was found dead on 8 October 1996 in [[Decatur, Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/news/nation-world/article/Prostitutes-grim-lives-end-violently-on-highway-1562282.php|title=Prostitutes' grim lives end violently on highway|work=Houston Chronicle|access-date=2017-09-23}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-02-09\"|1997\n|[[Murder of Amber Creek|Amber Creek]]\n|14\n|Amber Creek, a girl from [[Palatine, Illinois]] ran away from a youth shelter in January 1997, and was found dead on 9 February 1997, and was not identified until a year later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20140416/news/140418763/|title=Judge orders Eaton held over for trial in Amber Creek slaying|last=Graham|first=Doug T.|work=Daily Herald|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-06-28\"|1997\n|[[Gary DeVore]]\n|55\n|Gary DeVore, a Hollywood screenwriter best known for the movie ''[[Raw Deal (1986 film)|Raw Deal]]'', who disappeared on 28 June 1997, and a year later he and his car was discovered submerged in the [[California Aqueduct]] in [[Palmdale, California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/gq95k9/the-writer-with-no-hands-gary-devore-matthew-alford|title=The Mystery of the Dead Hollywood Screenwriter Whose Hands Were Never Found|website=Vice|language=en-uk|access-date=2017-09-17}}</ref>\n|No\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-11-07\"|1997\n|William Earl Moldt\n|40\n|William Moldt somehow drove his car unnoticed into the canal in the Grand Isles neighbohood of [[Lake Worth, Florida]] on 7 November 1997. His car was spotted by a man looking at a Google Earth image in late August, 2019 and his remains were recovered from the canal on 28 August of that year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Phillips Doug and Lois K. Solomon |first1=Doug and Lois K. Solomon |title=Google Earth uncovers car in pond \u2014 and skeleton of driver missing for 22 years |url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/local/palm-beach/wellington/fl-ne-missing-man-identified-wellington-20190912-tbuqkjl375ds7nijn6nl32cvu4-story.html |accessdate=26 October 2019 |work=South Florida Sun Sentinel |publisher=South Florida Sun-Sentinel |date=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n|No / Presumably drowned\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-11-14\"|1997\n|[[Murder of Reena Virk|Reena Virk]]\n|14\n|Reena Virk went missing on 14 November 1997 and was found dead on 22 November 1997, Warren Glowatski and Kelly Ellard were charged with murdering Virk and were found guilty.\n|No / Murdered\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1997-08-23\"|1998\n|[[Natascha Kampusch]]\n|10\n|Natascha Kampusch, an Austrian girl, who was kidnapped on her way to school in March 1998, was locked in a [[Basement|cellar]], and escaped on 23 August 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/5280472.stm|title=BBC NEWS {{!}} World {{!}} Europe {{!}} Austrian girl 'found' after years|website=news.bbc.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-08-08}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"1998-07-31\"|1998\n|[[Lois Roberts]]\n|3