und other suspicious aspects of the case suggesting the accident at the lake might have been staged and evidence planted; it was later investigated as a possible [[insurance fraud]].<ref name=\"Jerry Michael Williams\">{{cite news|last=Portman |first=Jennifer |title=Six years ago, this hunter disappeared |url=http://www.tallahassee.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20061215/NEWS01/102190004 |newspaper=[[Tallahassee Democrat]] |date=14 December 2006 |accessdate=8 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100226153618/http://www.tallahassee.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20061215%2FNEWS01%2F102190004 |archivedate=26 February 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2017 police announced his remains had been found, and that he was the victim of a [[homicide]], but gave no details.<ref name=\"Jerry Michael Williams found\">{{cite news|last=Portman|first=Jennifer|title=FLDE special agent: 'Mike Williams was murdered'|url=http://www.tallahassee.com/story/news/2017/12/20/fdle-give-update-mike-williams-disappearance/968920001|newspaper=[[Tallahassee Democrat]]|date=20 December 2017|accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref> On 8 May 2018, police arrested Williams' former wife, who had remarried. After a four-day trial in December 2018, she was convicted of murder, conspiracy, and accessory after the fact.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Etters|first1=Karl|last2=Portman|first2=Jennifer|title='Justice for Michael': 18 years later, Florida woman found guilty in plot to kill husband|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2018/12/14/denise-williams-trial-verdict-guilty-mike-williams-murder-case-jury/2319970002/|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|date=December 14, 2018|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|17 Years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2001-04-27|2001\n|[[Murder of Erica Green|Erica Green]]\n|data-sort-value=\"003\"|3\n|[[Murder]] victim whose [[Decapitation|decapitated]] body was discovered on 28 April 2001, in [[Kansas City, Missouri]], 12 to 48 hours after death. Her head was found in a trash bag nearby on 1 May 2001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2005/US/05/05/precious.doe/index.html|title=CNN.com \u2013 Mother, stepfather charged in 'Precious Doe' killing \u2013 May 5, 2005|website=www.cnn.com|access-date=2017-12-21}}</ref> The victim remained unidentified until 5 May 2005.\n|No / Murdered\n|1 - 2 days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2001-05-01|2001\n|[[Chandra Levy]]\n|data-sort-value=\"024\"|24\n|An American [[Internship|intern]] at the [[Federal Bureau of Prisons]] in Washington, D.C. who disappeared in May 2001. Her skeletal remains were found in [[Rock Creek Park]] on 22 May 2002.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2002/may/23/nation/na-chandra23|title=Remains in D.C. Park Identified as Intern's|last=BRAUN|first=STEPHEN|date=23 May 2002|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-08-14|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|1 Year\n|-\n|2001\n|Mananya Thumpong\n|13\n|Mananya Thumpong failed to return home from her local library in [[Sedan, Ardennes|Sedan]] on 5 May 2001. On 1 March 2002, her skeletal remains were found in a forest in [[Paliseul]]. [[Michel Fourniret]] confessed to kidnapping and killing her in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2008/04/30/la-mort-de-la-petite-asiatique-reperee-par-michel-fourniret_1040122_3224.html|title=La mort de la \"petite Asiatique\" rep\u00e9r\u00e9e par Michel Fourniret|date=30 April 2008|via=Le Monde}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|10 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2001-07-01|2001\n|[[Peter Falconio]]\n|data-sort-value=\"028\"|28\n|A British tourist from [[Hepworth, West Yorkshire|Hepworth]], West Yorkshire, who disappeared in the [[Australian outback]] in July 2001, while traveling with girlfriend [[Joanne Lees]]. Bradley Murdoch was charged with his disappearance, pleaded not guilty, but was convicted of the crime. He has appealed his conviction numerous times.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/news/national/lees-to-murdoch-wheres-the-body/2005/12/13/1134236063893.html|title=Murdoch guilty of murder: now tell us where the body is, says Lees \u2013 National|website=www.smh.com.au|language=en|access-date=2017-05-20}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2001-10-11|2001\n|Andrea Zabini\n|data-sort-value=\"032\"|32\n|An Italian national living in the United States disappeared in Aventura, Florida on October 11, after he left his girlfriend's house. His body had been found deceased in Miami the next day but remained unidentified until 2004 when a volunteer matched his \"John Doe\" record to the \"missing person record\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-xpm-2001-10-18-0110171329-story.html|title=POLICE FEAR MISSING MAN RAN INTO TROUBLE|website=sun-sentinel|access-date=2019-12-15}}</ref><ref>http://www.doenetwork.org/closedmain.php</ref><ref name=\"Halber 2015 p. 14\">{{cite book | last=Halber | first=D. | title=The Skeleton Crew: How Amateur Sleuths Are Solving America\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s Coldest Cases | publisher=Simon & Schuster | year=2015 | isbn=978-1-4516-5759-3 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5x5ICgAAQBAJ&pg=PA14 | language=fr | access-date=15 December 2019 | page=14}}</ref>\n|No / ?\n|1 day but not identified for 3 years\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2001-11-15|2001\n|[[Don Craig Wiley]]\n|data-sort-value=\"057\"|57\n|An American [[structural biologist]], who disappeared on 15 November 2001. His body was found in the [[Mississippi River]] a month later and his death was ruled to be an accident.<ref>{{cite web|title=Professor Don C. Wiley, 1944\u20132001|date=15 January 2002 |url=http://news.harvard.edu/specials/2001/wiley/|work=Office of news and public affairs|publisher=Harvard University|accessdate=15 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Harvard Biologist's Death Ruled Accidental|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/15/us/harvard-biologist-s-death-ruled-accidental.html|accessdate=15 November 2013|newspaper=The New York 