arance\" and contacted her family. She had been living in an isolated location, suffering from a physical ailment that caused her severe pain, and had not realized she was considered \"missing\".<ref name=\"psychologytoday.com\">Mike Martin, [http://www.psychologytoday.com/articles/201204/the-mysterious-case-the-vanishing-genius The Mysterious Case of the Vanishing Genius]. ''Psychology Today'', May 2012.</ref><ref name=\"blogs.nature.com\">Brendan Maher, [http://blogs.nature.com/news/2012/05/missing-biologist-surfaces-reunites-with-family.html Missing Biologist Surfaces, Reunites with Family.] ''Nature'', 31 May 2012.</ref>\n|Yes\n|7 Years out of contact\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2005-02-24\" |2005\n|[[Murder of Jessica Lunsford|Jessica Lunsford]]\n| data-sort-value=\"009\" |9\n|An American girl who was abducted from her home in [[Homosassa, Florida]] in the early morning of 24 February 2005 by John Couey; her body was found three weeks later, buried at the home of Couey's half-sister, who lived within sight of the Lunsford home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/CRIME/09/30/florida.couey.dead/|title=Convicted child killer Couey dies in prison, Florida officials say - CNN.com|website=www.cnn.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-23}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|3 Weeks\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2005-06-30\" |2005\n|[[Patrick McDermott]]\n| data-sort-value=\"048\" |48\n|American cameraman and former boyfriend of singer [[Olivia Newton-John]]; disappeared from a fishing charter boat off [[San Pedro, Los Angeles]], on 30 June 2005, and was suspected of faking his own death in order to cash in on a $100,000 life insurance policy for his son. However, a [[United States Coast Guard]] investigation released in November 2008 concluded that McDermott most likely drowned.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/story/0,,24973799-10230,00.html |title=Patrick McDermott is Alive and on the Run |work=News.com.au |date=28 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveur