es, that were found half a mile from the crash site, probably scattered by wild animals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/US/10/02/steve.fossett.search/index.html|title=Some remains found in Fossett plane wreckage - CNN.com|website=www.cnn.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/3125782/Body-parts-found-in-wreckage-of-Steve-Fossetts-plane.html|title='Body parts' found in wreckage of Steve Fossett's plane|last=York|first=By Tom Leonard in New|work=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2017-05-13|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Plane crash\n|1 Year\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2008-01-20\" |2008\n|[[Murder of Brianna Denison|Brianna Denison]]\n| data-sort-value=\"019\" |19\n|A college student from [[Santa Barbara, California]], who was abducted on 20 January 2008 from a friend's house in [[Reno, Nevada]]. Her body was discovered on 15 February 2008 in a field near a Reno business park after being raped and murdered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/CRIME/12/02/cold.case.arrest/index.html|title=Tip line played key role in cracking cold case - CNN.com|last=Producer|first=By Rupa Mikkilineni Nancy Grace|website=www.cnn.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-21}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|26 Days\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2008-02-19\" |2008\n|[[Kidnapping of Shannon Matthews|Shannon Matthews]]\n| data-sort-value=\"009\" |9\n|English girl who was kidnapped in [[Dewsbury|Dewsbury, West Yorkshire]] on 19 February 2008.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-38881419|title=Shannon Matthews: The kidnap hoax that shocked the UK|date=6 February 2017|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-08-11|language=en-GB}}</ref> She was found alive and well on 14 March 2008, and it turned out that the \"kidnapping\" had been a scam by her mother and an uncle of the mother's boyfriend to fraudulently claim a reward for her return.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/02/07/what-happened-to-shannon-matthew