oy, her former boyfriend, was detained by [[Lothian and Borders Police]] under section 14 of the [[Criminal Procedure Act#Scotland|Criminal Procedure (Scotland) Act 1995]] in connection with her disappearance. Later that day he was arrested and charged with her murder,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://forargyll.com/2010/06/suzanne-pilley-murder-david-gilroy-in-police-detention/ |title=Argyll News: Suzanne Pilley murder: David Gilroy in police detention, now charged |publisher=For Argyll |date=23 June 2010 |accessdate=26 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100629022608/http://forargyll.com/2010/06/suzanne-pilley-murder-david-gilroy-in-police-detention/ |archive-date=29 June 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and on 15 March 2012 he was found guilty, revealing that she had been murdered.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-edinburgh-east-fife-17367652 |title=Suzanne Pilley murder trial: David Gilroy found guilty |publisher=BBC News |date=15 March 2012 |accessdate=26 July 2012}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n|2010\n|[[Murders of Lyle and Marie McCann|Lyle and Marie McCann]]\n|78 (Lyle)<br>77 (Marie)\n|The McCann couple, from [[St. Albert, Alberta]], Canada, went missing after going on a road trip on 3 July 2010. Their bodies were never found. In January 2017, Travis Vader was sentenced to life imprisonment for their manslaughter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2016/10/31/travis-vader-murder-verdict-changed-to-manslaughter-as-judge-admits-error.html|title=Travis Vader murder verdict changed to manslaughter as judge admits error|access-date=2016-10-31}}</ref>\n|No / Manslaughter\n|Not Found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2010-07-19\"|2010\n|[[Lorenzen Wright]]\n|data-sort-value=\"034\"|34\n|An American professional [[basketball]] player, who disappeared on 19 July 2010, and was found dead on 28 July in [[Memphis, Tennessee]], in a wooded area. The case was ruled a homicide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sp