 life sentence for murder of Elaine O'Hara|publisher=BBC News|date=20 April 2015}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|1 Year\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2012-10-01\"|2012\n|[[Murder of April Jones|April Jones]]\n|data-sort-value=\"006\"|5\n|A girl from [[Machynlleth|Machynlleth, Powys]], who disappeared after she was sighted willingly getting into a vehicle near her home on 1 October 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/blog/2012/oct/02/april-jones-missing-five-live|title=April Jones: police search for missing five-year-old|last=Davies|first=Lizzy|date=2 October 2012|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-08-06|last2=Walker|first2=Peter|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|last3=Quinn|first3=Ben}}</ref> On 30 May 2013, Mark Bridger was convicted of Jones' abduction and murder,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2013/may/30/april-jones-murder-final-hours|title=April Jones murder: how detectives pieced together her final hours|last=Morris|first=Steven|date=30 May 2013|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-08-06|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> after forensic evidence was found in his car and home but her body has never been found.\n|No / Murdered\n|Not Found\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2012-12-20\"|2012\n|[[Tokbergen Abiyev]]\n|data-sort-value=\"005\"|unknown\n|A [[Kazakhs|Kazakh]] journalist who went missing on 20 December 2012, just hours after he announced to the Kazakh media that he had a sensational news report about to be published.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpj.org/2012/12/journalist-press-club-founder-disappears-in-kazakh.php|title=Journalist, press club founder disappears in Kazakhstan|publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists|date=27 December 2012|accessdate=28 December 2012}}</ref> Abiyev reappeared on 4 January 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/missing-journalist-reappears-freedom-information-doesnt|title=\"Missing\" journalist reappears, but freedom of information doesn't {{!}} Reporters without borders|website=RSF|language=fr-