\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2013-04-26\"|2013\n|[[Murder of Jessica Heeringa|Jessica Heeringa]]\n|data-sort-value=\"025\"|25\n|Heeringa disappeared from her job at a gas station in [[Norton Shores, Michigan]] on 26 April 2013. Although her remains have not been found, in 2016, Jeffrey Willis, a frequent customer of hers, was charged with her kidnapping and murder due to forensic evidence and eyewitness testimony, while his cousin Kevin Bluhm was charged with accessory after the fact after he confessed to helping him bury her body.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.woodtv.com/news/muskegon-county/prosecutor-to-give-update-on-jessica-heeringa-case/1003529564 |title=Jeffrey Willis charged with murdering Jessica Heeringa |publisher=WOOD-TV |date=20 September 2016 |first=Rikki Jo |last=Holmes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=VanTimmeren|first1=Christine|title=Court documents reveal disturbing new information in Jessica Heeringa case|url=http://wwmt.com/news/local/court-documents-reveal-disturbing-new-information-in-jessica-heeringa-case|accessdate=5 January 2017|work=WWMT}}</ref> Willis was found guilty of Heeringa's kidnapping and murder on 16 May 2018.<ref>[http://www.mlive.com/news/muskegon/index.ssf/2018/05/jeffrey_willis_found_guilty_of.html Jeffrey Willis found guilty of kidnapping, murdering Jessica Heeringa] ''The Muskegon Chronicle'' via MLive.com, May 16, 2018</ref> He received a life sentence without parole a month later.<ref>[http://www.woodtv.com/news/jeffrey-willis-investigation/willis-claims-innocence-at-heeringa-murder-sentence/1230498914 Willis claims innocence at Heeringa murder sentence] WOOD-TV, June 18, 2018</ref> On 27 November 2017, Bluhm pleaded no contest to being an accessory after the fact for helping Willis dispose of Heeringa's body and was sentenced on 9 January 2018 to time served, plus five years probation and to wear a GPS tether for at least a year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin Bluhm walks free for his role in Jessica Heeringa's murder|url=http://