 former quarterback Cullen Finnerty could expand, and Grand Valley State ready to help|author=|date=|website=mlive.com}}</ref>\n|No / Pneumonia\n|2 Days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-01-11\"|2014\n|[[David Bird (journalist)|David Bird]]\n|data-sort-value=\"055\"|55\n|Bird, a reporter for the ''[[Wall Street Journal]]'', left his [[Millington, New Jersey]], home for a short walk on 11 January 2014, and never returned. His body was found in a nearby river 14 months later. A subsequent investigation determined that the [[cause of death]] was accidental drowning.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.com/story/news/local/2015/06/09/death-david-bird-long-hill-ruled-drowning/28756505/|title=Death of David Bird in Long Hill ruled a drowning|work=Daily Record|access-date=2017-03-25|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Drowning\n|14 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-01-11\"|2014\n|[[Deaths of Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon|Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon]]\n|data-sort-value=\"021\"|21 and 22\n|Two [[Dutch people|Dutch]] students who disappeared on 1 April 2014, while hiking in [[Panama]]. Their remains were found on 22 June 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nltimes.nl/2014/06/23/remains-found-panama-lisanne-froons/|title=Remains found in Panama are Lisanne Froon's|date=23 June 2014|work=NL Times|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en}}</ref> There are unanswered questions about their deaths and it has not been possible to rule out accident or murder.\n|No / Death by misadventure\n|9 Weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-07-08\"|2014\n|[[Death of Lynn Messer|Lynn Messer]]\n|data-sort-value=\"052\"|52\n|Messer was not in bed next to her husband when he awoke on the morning of 8 July 2014, at their farm in [[Bloomsdale, Missouri]]. All her personal effects, including a walking boot she had been wearing to protect her broken toe, were in the house.<ref name=\"Lynn Messer\">{{cite web|url=http://stlouis.cbslocal.com/2015/07/07/one-year-later-more-questions-in-case-of-missing-mo-woman/|title=