-13\"|2014\n|[[Murder of Hannah Graham|Hannah Graham]]\n|data-sort-value=\"018\"|18\n|Graham was reported missing after last being seen at the [[Downtown Mall]] in [[Charlottesville, Virginia]] on 13 September 2014, and her remains were found on 18 October 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbc29.com/story/26886621/medical-examiner-confirms-hannah-grahams-remains-found-in-albemarle|title=Medical Examiner Confirms Hannah Graham's Remains Found in Albemarle|access-date=2017-05-30|language=en}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|5 Weeks\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-10-22|2014\n|[[Death of Atsumi Yoshikubo|Atsumi Yoshikubo]]\n|data-sort-value=\"045\"|45\n|Yoshikubo, a Japanese psychiatrist, was last seen on the morning of 22 October 2014, walking along the [[Ingraham Trail]] (NT 4) in a wooded area on the northern outskirts of [[Yellowknife|Yellowknife, Northwest Territories]], Canada. Her disappearance was not noted until three days later, when she had failed to check out of her hotel and the staff found her luggage, all packed, in her room. An intense search both by the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) and concerned local residents over the next few days was called off after a week when the RCMP announced that their investigation had led them to conclude that she came to Yellowknife with the intent to disappear into the wilderness (although she had bought a return ticket to Japan and souvenirs).<ref>{{cite news|last=O'Connor|first=Joe|title=RCMP believes Japanese psychiatrist had suicidal plan to disappear into wilderness outside Yellowknife|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/news/canada/rcmp-believe-missing-japanese-psychiatrist-had-suicidal-plan-to-disappear-into-wilderness-outside-yellowknife|newspaper=[[National Post]]|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> Ten months later a hunter discovered some of her personal effects along with human remains in [[the bush]] off the highway; on April 14, 2016, those remains were positively identified as Yoshikubo's.<ref>{{cite news|title=DNA confirms remains found in 2015 belong to Atsumi Yoshikubo, missing Japanese tourist|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/north/atsumi-yoshikubo-dna-confirms-id-human-remains-1.3536268|newspaper=CBC|date=14 April 2016|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n|No\n|10 Months\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2014-06-16|2014\n|[[Disappearance of Charles Bothuell V|Charles Bothuell V]]\n|data-sort-value=\"012\"|12\n|An American boy from [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]], reported missing by his father in June 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2015/02/20/parents-boy-held-basement-charged-torture/23779195/|title=Parents of boy held in basement charged with torture|work=USA TODAY|access-date=2017-08-09|language=en}}</ref> When a search was conducted to find him, he was found alive eleven days later locked in his parents' basement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/detroit-boy-found-in-basement-says-his-home-was-terrible/|accessdate=10 October 2017|title=Detroit boy found in basement says his home was \"terrible\"|date=28 April 2015|publisher=CBS News \u2013 cbsnews.com}}</ref>\n|Yes\n|11 Days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2015-02-19\"|2015\n|[[Murder of Becky Watts|Becky Watts]]\n|data-sort-value=\"016\"|16\n|Watts, from Crown Hill in the [[St George, Bristol|St George]] area of Bristol, England, went missing on 19 February 2015. Her [[dismemberment|dismembered]] body was found on 3 March 2015 in [[Bristol|Barton Court]], Bristol.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-31709056|title=Body parts found in Becky search|date=3 March 2015|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-09-15|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|No / Murdered\n|12 Days\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2015-01-01\"|2015\n|[[Bella Bond murder case|Bella Bond]]\n|data-sort-value=\"002\"|2\n|A child who was found dead in a plastic bag on the shore of [[Deer Island (Massachusetts)|Deer Island]] in [[Winthrop, Massachusetts]], on 25 June 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://w